1
00:00:14,014 --> 00:00:17,150
First of all, a celebration is due.

2
00:00:17,217 --> 00:00:19,686
There's an award
called the Oscars of culinary world.

3
00:00:20,286 --> 00:00:23,656
<i>It's called Asia's 50 Best Restaurants,</i>

4
00:00:23,723 --> 00:00:25,625
<i>and the ceremony was</i>
<i>recently held in Seoul.</i>

5
00:00:25,692 --> 00:00:28,194
It's a very prestigious event as well.

6
00:00:28,261 --> 00:00:31,264
And among these 50 restaurants,

7
00:00:31,331 --> 00:00:35,135
four Korean restaurants
made it to the list.

8
00:00:35,201 --> 00:00:38,138
Among those four,

9
00:00:38,204 --> 00:00:41,975
Chef Jong-won's restaurant
was placed in 25th.

10
00:00:42,942 --> 00:00:44,310
He's the 25th place.

11
00:00:44,377 --> 00:00:46,813
Son Jong-won!

12
00:00:46,880 --> 00:00:48,948
You were 25th place among 50.

13
00:00:49,015 --> 00:00:50,917
-We're sitting with an amazing man.
-We are.

14
00:00:50,984 --> 00:00:52,752
It was his first time
making it on the list.

15
00:00:52,819 --> 00:00:56,656
And because he got to 25th place
from 64th place last year,

16
00:00:56,723 --> 00:00:59,426
he was also awarded
the Highest New Entry Award.

17
00:00:59,492 --> 00:01:02,128
-So he became 25th as soon as he moved up?
-Yes.

18
00:01:02,195 --> 00:01:03,696
-He skyrocketed.
-He's the pride of <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>.

19
00:01:03,763 --> 00:01:05,398
Not only is he our pride,

20
00:01:05,465 --> 00:01:09,536
-but we thought we helped a bit.
-Yes, that's true.

21
00:01:09,602 --> 00:01:11,604
-He can't say we didn't play a role.
-No.

22
00:01:11,671 --> 00:01:15,308
Right? We were the ones
who told people about Jong-won.

23
00:01:15,375 --> 00:01:18,745
He's now the most famous Son
after Son Goku.

24
00:01:18,812 --> 00:01:20,680
I do believe
<i>Chef & My Fridge</i> played a role.

25
00:01:20,747 --> 00:01:22,949
-Right?
-Thank you.

26
00:01:23,016 --> 00:01:24,851
And because the event was held in Korea,

27
00:01:24,918 --> 00:01:29,055
<i>many amazing chefs</i>
<i>traveled here to participate.</i>

28
00:01:29,122 --> 00:01:30,757
<i>And among those chefs,</i>

29
00:01:30,824 --> 00:01:33,426
<i>Chef & My Fridge </i>was such a hot potato.

30
00:01:33,493 --> 00:01:35,462
-Really?
-Yes.

31
00:01:35,528 --> 00:01:37,430
That's why we prepared a special episode.

32
00:01:37,497 --> 00:01:38,498
That's right!

33
00:01:38,565 --> 00:01:41,101
-I didn't know this would come true.
-I didn't, either.

34
00:01:41,167 --> 00:01:44,170
Chefs of <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>
versus top Asian chefs.

35
00:01:44,237 --> 00:01:47,207
We're going to hold
this big competition today!

36
00:01:47,273 --> 00:01:50,443
Please welcome these top Asian chefs!

37
00:01:50,510 --> 00:01:52,378
Come on out!

38
00:01:55,682 --> 00:01:57,684
WHICH CHEFS JOINED
THE SHOW TODAY?

39
00:01:59,786 --> 00:02:01,354
WELCOMING THEM WITH EXCITEMENT

40
00:02:01,921 --> 00:02:04,591
A TEAM OF TOP CHEFS IN ASIA!

41
00:02:05,158 --> 00:02:07,260
…OR SO WE HEARD

42
00:02:08,061 --> 00:02:10,530
-Please welcome these chefs.
-Wait.

43
00:02:10,597 --> 00:02:13,032
-What's he doing here?
-Something seems odd.

44
00:02:13,099 --> 00:02:14,834
-Wait, why is he here?
-I don't think you're a chef.

45
00:02:14,901 --> 00:02:17,203
-Did you get the wrong casting call?
-Wait.

46
00:02:17,270 --> 00:02:18,605
-Why?
-Are you supposed to be here?

47
00:02:18,671 --> 00:02:21,407
-You're the Prince of Asia, right?
-I am.

48
00:02:21,474 --> 00:02:23,343
Asia's best prince.

49
00:02:23,409 --> 00:02:27,747
Asia's knockout chef,
well, for now, Jang Keun-suk.

50
00:02:27,814 --> 00:02:30,617
For now, Keun-suk is here.

51
00:02:30,683 --> 00:02:33,019
-Welcome.
-Keun-suk is here.

52
00:02:33,086 --> 00:02:34,988
We'll ask him what's up later.

53
00:02:35,054 --> 00:02:36,289
Let me introduce the next chef.

54
00:02:36,356 --> 00:02:38,725
The 8th place
of Asia's 50 Best Restaurants,

55
00:02:38,791 --> 00:02:41,528
<i>the chef of a two-star Michelin</i>
<i>restaurant in Osaka,</i>

56
00:02:41,594 --> 00:02:43,062
please welcome Chef Yusuke Takada.

57
00:02:43,129 --> 00:02:45,565
Welcome to the show, Chef Yusuke!

58
00:02:46,566 --> 00:02:47,734
He took eighth place.

59
00:02:47,800 --> 00:02:48,902
He's my role model.

60
00:02:48,968 --> 00:02:52,305
-He's one of the top ten.
-Yes, he is. He's an amazing chef.

61
00:02:52,372 --> 00:02:54,407
Let me introduce you
to the chef next to him.

62
00:02:54,474 --> 00:02:57,210
This chef took 37th place
in Asia's 50 Best Restaurants.

63
00:02:57,277 --> 00:02:59,612
<i>A chef of a one-star Michelin</i>
<i>restaurant in Singapore,</i>

64
00:02:59,679 --> 00:03:01,681
please welcome Chef Han Li Guang!

65
00:03:01,748 --> 00:03:03,583
Welcome to the show.

66
00:03:03,650 --> 00:03:05,318
WELCOME

67
00:03:05,385 --> 00:03:08,087
Next, in 32nd place
of Asia's 50 Best Restaurants,

68
00:03:08,154 --> 00:03:10,023
please welcome Chef Antimo Maria Merone!

69
00:03:10,089 --> 00:03:11,891
-Chef Antimo!
-Welcome to the show.

70
00:03:11,958 --> 00:03:13,927
Forza Italia!

71
00:03:13,993 --> 00:03:16,396
EXCITED TO MEET
A FELLOW ITALIAN OVERSEAS

72
00:03:16,462 --> 00:03:19,465
My source says he's an actual Neapolitan.

73
00:03:19,532 --> 00:03:20,867
He is?

74
00:03:24,037 --> 00:03:25,338
He's an actual Neapolitan.

75
00:03:25,405 --> 00:03:27,173
The fake Neapolitan
and the real Neapolitan!

76
00:03:27,240 --> 00:03:28,374
-The fake Neapolitan.
-The real Neapolitan?

77
00:03:28,441 --> 00:03:32,145
-He's from Italy, but…
-I am, but I'm not from…

78
00:03:33,780 --> 00:03:35,481
INTRIGUED

79
00:03:36,049 --> 00:03:37,750
NICE TO HAVE YOU HERE

80
00:03:37,817 --> 00:03:39,819
A PATRIOTIC HUG

81
00:03:39,886 --> 00:03:42,889
Keun-suk is here with us for
the Asia's 50 Best Restaurants special.

82
00:03:42,956 --> 00:03:44,958
-I was surprised too.
-Right?

83
00:03:45,024 --> 00:03:47,427
Is he seriously here to do this?

84
00:03:47,493 --> 00:03:48,695
What brings you here?

85
00:03:48,761 --> 00:03:50,830
I'm nicknamed Asia's Prince, right?

86
00:03:50,897 --> 00:03:53,933
So I came here as their guide
and escorted them here safely.

87
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:56,569
-That's why I'm here.
-I see.

88
00:03:56,636 --> 00:03:59,973
Anyway, in that case,
will you be competing today?

89
00:04:00,039 --> 00:04:03,209
They may be top chefs in Asia,

90
00:04:03,276 --> 00:04:07,213
but even these chefs found one man
to be a tough competition.

91
00:04:07,280 --> 00:04:10,250
If you call his cooking style
the knockoff,

92
00:04:10,316 --> 00:04:13,219
then I wanted to be here as a knockout.

93
00:04:13,286 --> 00:04:14,287
-I see.
-Me?

94
00:04:14,354 --> 00:04:17,857
I wanted to show off
the skills I've mastered at home.

95
00:04:17,924 --> 00:04:19,492
All right. I got you.

96
00:04:19,559 --> 00:04:22,562
Do you see their red scarves?

97
00:04:22,629 --> 00:04:25,999
These scarves are
only awarded to the chefs

98
00:04:26,065 --> 00:04:29,902
<i>who make the top 50 restaurants</i>
<i>in the event.</i>

99
00:04:29,969 --> 00:04:32,438
Keun-suk, yours is a little different.

100
00:04:32,505 --> 00:04:34,841
-It looks thick.
-It's grayish.

101
00:04:34,907 --> 00:04:38,111
-I felt a bit chilly.
-Where did you…

102
00:04:38,177 --> 00:04:40,513
-Isn't that a piano key cover?
-A piano cover.

103
00:04:40,580 --> 00:04:41,581
It's warm.

104
00:04:42,782 --> 00:04:43,783
-It looks real.
-Really?

105
00:04:43,850 --> 00:04:46,352
The production crew said
it was a real piano key cover.

106
00:04:46,419 --> 00:04:49,088
-Are you serious?
-Yeah, that's a real piano key cover.

107
00:04:49,155 --> 00:04:52,225
I'd feel left out if I didn't have one,
so I wanted to fit in.

108
00:04:52,292 --> 00:04:54,227
Shouldn't you have one too?

109
00:04:55,161 --> 00:04:57,096
-Do you have it?
-Why aren't you wearing it?

110
00:04:57,163 --> 00:05:00,600
-He gets really shy. Put it on.
-He has it.

111
00:05:00,667 --> 00:05:02,468
He was the 25th place.

112
00:05:02,535 --> 00:05:05,772
-Put it on yourself.
-Come on, don't be shy.

113
00:05:05,838 --> 00:05:07,707
You made it
into Asia's 50 Best Restaurants.

114
00:05:07,774 --> 00:05:09,609
-The 25th place.
-It looks great on him.

115
00:05:09,676 --> 00:05:13,079
-That scarf isn't for anyone. Looks great.
-It does.

116
00:05:13,146 --> 00:05:14,847
It feels nice.

117
00:05:14,914 --> 00:05:18,651
-Is this made of cashmere?
-Stop touching it.

118
00:05:18,718 --> 00:05:21,154
-I wanted to know how it felt.
-Come on.

119
00:05:21,220 --> 00:05:24,424
Stop it, Fabri. Have some manners.

120
00:05:24,490 --> 00:05:27,660
-I want to make it onto the list.
-Put that down.

121
00:05:27,727 --> 00:05:29,095
First of all,

122
00:05:29,162 --> 00:05:31,631
number eight, Chef Yusuke.

123
00:05:31,698 --> 00:05:34,934
I hear there's someone here
who has Chef Yusuke as a role model.

124
00:05:35,001 --> 00:05:37,337
He follows him on social media
and leaves comments too.

125
00:05:37,403 --> 00:05:40,073
-I see.
-I heard someone is crushing on him.

126
00:05:40,139 --> 00:05:42,542
Which one of our chefs has
Chef Yusuke as the role model?

127
00:05:42,608 --> 00:05:44,977
-It's Nam-no?
-Really?

128
00:05:45,044 --> 00:05:46,779
They have similar styles.

129
00:05:46,846 --> 00:05:48,981
-Look at their hair color.
-Yes, the hair color.

130
00:05:49,048 --> 00:05:50,383
-Right?
-He copied him.

131
00:05:50,450 --> 00:05:52,985
-I didn't know.
-I wanted to be like him in 15 years,

132
00:05:53,052 --> 00:05:54,454
with those glasses and all.

133
00:05:54,520 --> 00:05:56,789
The type of food I want to…

134
00:05:56,856 --> 00:05:58,391
I'm sorry. I'm so nervous right now.

135
00:05:58,458 --> 00:06:00,293
You must be.

136
00:06:00,360 --> 00:06:02,228
I didn't expect to see him here.

137
00:06:02,295 --> 00:06:03,930
That was Chef Yusuke.

138
00:06:03,996 --> 00:06:06,566
Do you want to put on glasses
with a chain like him?

139
00:06:07,500 --> 00:06:09,602
You'll look more like him
if you grow out your mustache.

140
00:06:09,669 --> 00:06:12,472
Yes, they have a similar style.
He just called him a role model.

141
00:06:12,538 --> 00:06:13,740
Put the chain behind you.

142
00:06:13,806 --> 00:06:16,242
He's putting on
a world-renowned chef's glasses.

143
00:06:17,410 --> 00:06:19,946
A MASTER

144
00:06:20,012 --> 00:06:22,715
-You look great.
-You look like a master chef.

145
00:06:22,782 --> 00:06:25,752
-They suit you.
-You should grow out a mustache too.

146
00:06:25,818 --> 00:06:27,987
I had gray hair on <i>Culinary Class Wars</i>,

147
00:06:28,054 --> 00:06:30,022
and I did that to copy him.

148
00:06:30,089 --> 00:06:32,458
-You did?
-I really copied him.

149
00:06:32,525 --> 00:06:35,695
-I couldn't grow out my mustache quickly.
-I see.

150
00:06:35,762 --> 00:06:39,098
Next up, 37th place
of Asia's 50 Best Restaurants,

151
00:06:39,165 --> 00:06:41,334
please welcome Chef Han Li Guang.

152
00:06:41,401 --> 00:06:44,270
According to our sources,

153
00:06:44,337 --> 00:06:48,441
people call Chef Li Guang
the Choi Hyun-suk of Singapore.

154
00:06:48,508 --> 00:06:50,643
-Is he a showoff?
-Is he a showoff?

155
00:06:50,710 --> 00:06:53,246
It's not that.
About seven to eight years ago,

156
00:06:53,312 --> 00:06:54,947
I ate at his restaurant.

157
00:06:55,014 --> 00:06:56,549
We have a similar style of cooking.

158
00:07:05,124 --> 00:07:07,927
He's wearing the symbols
of the most famous Singaporean dish.

159
00:07:07,994 --> 00:07:10,430
-Chili and crab.
-I see.

160
00:07:10,496 --> 00:07:12,865
-Chili and crab, chili crab.
-Yes, chili crab.

161
00:07:12,932 --> 00:07:14,233
Chili crab.

162
00:07:14,300 --> 00:07:15,768
Chili crab is really famous.

163
00:07:15,835 --> 00:07:18,604
LI GUANG IS A FUN GUY

164
00:07:18,671 --> 00:07:21,107
This next chef is extraordinary.

165
00:07:21,174 --> 00:07:24,377
-He almost looks like a movie actor.
-He does.

166
00:07:24,444 --> 00:07:26,979
The 32nd place
among Asia's 50 Best Restaurants.

167
00:07:27,046 --> 00:07:30,883
A real Neapolitan, Chef Antimo.

168
00:07:30,950 --> 00:07:32,151
Hello.

169
00:07:33,019 --> 00:07:34,821
He's a very passionate guy.

170
00:07:34,887 --> 00:07:37,857
He watched every single episode
he could find

171
00:07:37,924 --> 00:07:39,992
on the streaming platform.

172
00:07:40,059 --> 00:07:42,228
-Really?
-Is this true?

173
00:07:44,063 --> 00:07:45,932
PREPARED HIMSELF THOROUGHLY!

174
00:07:45,998 --> 00:07:49,569
I heard he picked up a Korean word
while watching <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>.

175
00:07:49,635 --> 00:07:52,138
-Did you learn Korean while watching us?
-What is it?

176
00:07:54,173 --> 00:07:56,042
Mr. Good Vibes.

177
00:07:56,108 --> 00:07:58,311
-Mr. Good Vibes?
-Mr. Good Vibes?

178
00:07:58,377 --> 00:08:00,379
-He picked up Mr. Good Vibes?
-Mr. Good Vibes.

179
00:08:00,446 --> 00:08:04,183
-He also has a Korean colleague.
-Mr. Good Vibes.

180
00:08:09,188 --> 00:08:12,692
We'd look at him and go, "Mr. Good Vibes."

181
00:08:12,758 --> 00:08:14,260
Mr. Good Vibes.

182
00:08:14,327 --> 00:08:16,229
I think we can leave Fabri out

183
00:08:16,295 --> 00:08:17,797
starting next episode.

184
00:08:17,864 --> 00:08:20,633
-We can invite Chef Antimo.
-Isn't he fun?

185
00:08:20,700 --> 00:08:23,035
-He's funny.
-Chef Antimo is a fun guy.

186
00:08:23,102 --> 00:08:25,738
He can give us good marketing too.

187
00:08:30,409 --> 00:08:32,612
-We don't need two Italians.
-No.

188
00:08:32,678 --> 00:08:37,450
It's now time to invite the fridge owners

189
00:08:37,517 --> 00:08:40,586
who'll be the judge of this big match.

190
00:08:40,653 --> 00:08:44,090
These are two superstars of Asia.

191
00:08:44,156 --> 00:08:47,760
Please welcome today's fridge owners.
Come on out!

192
00:08:48,327 --> 00:08:49,795
Today's fridge owners.

193
00:08:50,830 --> 00:08:52,532
Who will it be?

194
00:08:52,598 --> 00:08:54,066
All right!

195
00:08:54,133 --> 00:08:55,134
CHEERING

196
00:08:56,536 --> 00:08:59,872
These are the fridge owners
who came to join us today.

197
00:08:59,939 --> 00:09:01,440
The superstars of Asia,

198
00:09:01,507 --> 00:09:04,544
please welcome
Kim Jae-joong and Choo Sung-hoon!

199
00:09:04,610 --> 00:09:06,112
Come on in.

200
00:09:06,178 --> 00:09:08,915
-Hello.
-Please take your seat.

201
00:09:08,981 --> 00:09:10,650
-Have you been well?
-Yes.

202
00:09:14,086 --> 00:09:16,389
Why are you here?

203
00:09:16,455 --> 00:09:18,391
Are you here as a chef?

204
00:09:18,457 --> 00:09:20,927
-He's huge.
-He's like a mafia boss.

205
00:09:20,993 --> 00:09:24,797
Sung-hoon keeps losing another
button whenever he joins us.

206
00:09:24,864 --> 00:09:26,365
Next time, you'll come without a shirt.

207
00:09:26,432 --> 00:09:29,001
-Always.
-Always ready.

208
00:09:29,068 --> 00:09:30,770
If I may tell you about Sung-hoon,

209
00:09:30,836 --> 00:09:32,438
he's the first to come the third time.

210
00:09:32,505 --> 00:09:36,509
<i>Only he has this record,</i>
<i>which makes him practically our family.</i>

211
00:09:36,576 --> 00:09:38,277
-He's a regular.
-He is.

212
00:09:38,344 --> 00:09:42,648
Sung-hoon, I believe you are acquainted
with both Jae-joong and Keun-suk.

213
00:09:42,715 --> 00:09:43,716
Totally.

214
00:09:43,783 --> 00:09:47,587
-We've been friends for… Over a decade?
-Yes, over a decade.

215
00:09:47,653 --> 00:09:50,590
We've been friends for a long time,
and we often got wasted together.

216
00:09:50,656 --> 00:09:53,626
Yes, we used to get pissed.

217
00:09:53,693 --> 00:09:57,930
-But Keun-suk is one of the chefs today.
-I heard.

218
00:09:57,997 --> 00:10:00,666
There were a few times
when he'd cook for me,

219
00:10:00,733 --> 00:10:02,969
so I've tried his food,

220
00:10:03,035 --> 00:10:04,337
and he's good.

221
00:10:04,403 --> 00:10:06,772
I have high expectations today.

222
00:10:06,839 --> 00:10:07,907
He's that good?

223
00:10:07,974 --> 00:10:10,876
Keun-suk cooked for me a few times too.

224
00:10:10,943 --> 00:10:13,879
He's a good cook,
and he can make many different types.

225
00:10:13,946 --> 00:10:15,481
Honestly speaking,

226
00:10:15,548 --> 00:10:17,116
I think Jae-joong has more pride

227
00:10:17,183 --> 00:10:20,620
when it comes to cooking,

228
00:10:20,686 --> 00:10:23,089
-even more than Poong.
-Really?

229
00:10:23,155 --> 00:10:24,924
-Is he proud of his cooking skills?
-Totally.

230
00:10:24,991 --> 00:10:26,959
HE ADMITS RIGHT AWAY

231
00:10:27,026 --> 00:10:30,429
I've published a few cookbooks already.

232
00:10:30,496 --> 00:10:32,331
-Is that so?
-That's true.

233
00:10:32,398 --> 00:10:34,767
You have some insight in this field.

234
00:10:34,834 --> 00:10:36,302
-I love to cook.
-In that case,

235
00:10:36,369 --> 00:10:40,072
let's take a look at Jae-joong's fridge.

236
00:10:40,139 --> 00:10:41,674
Wait a second. What are these?

237
00:10:41,741 --> 00:10:44,410
These are…
Why do you have carrot tops here?

238
00:10:44,477 --> 00:10:46,012
-What are these?
-Those are mushrooms.

239
00:10:46,078 --> 00:10:47,079
What are these?

240
00:10:47,146 --> 00:10:49,215
I've been growing those.

241
00:10:49,281 --> 00:10:50,349
What?

242
00:10:50,416 --> 00:10:51,884
You're growing these?

243
00:10:51,951 --> 00:10:55,988
If you cut off carrot tops
and leave it in a dish with water,

244
00:10:56,055 --> 00:10:58,024
the leaves will begin to grow.

245
00:10:58,090 --> 00:11:02,061
I heard carrot leaves were
more nutritious than the orange part.

246
00:11:02,128 --> 00:11:04,530
Do you grow these, cut them,
and then eat them too?

247
00:11:04,597 --> 00:11:05,831
Yes, I use them like parsley.

248
00:11:05,898 --> 00:11:08,034
-I see.
-I see.

249
00:11:08,100 --> 00:11:10,703
This was the first time I heard that.

250
00:11:10,770 --> 00:11:12,538
Can the chefs use these?

251
00:11:12,605 --> 00:11:14,106
Yes, they're organic.

252
00:11:14,173 --> 00:11:16,509
Yes, these are completely organic.

253
00:11:16,575 --> 00:11:18,678
That sounds great. All right, then.

254
00:11:18,744 --> 00:11:21,647
-Let's take a look at Jae-joong's fridge.
-Jae-joong's fridge.

255
00:11:21,714 --> 00:11:23,082
-Jae-joong's fridge.
-Jae-joong's fridge.

256
00:11:23,149 --> 00:11:24,984
-Whoa.
-My gosh.

257
00:11:25,551 --> 00:11:27,653
PRESENTING JAE-JOONG'S FRIDGE

258
00:11:28,387 --> 00:11:30,256
-That's a lot.
-He has lots of kimchi.

259
00:11:30,322 --> 00:11:31,757
Hey, the sauces.

260
00:11:31,824 --> 00:11:33,659
-The top two shelves are red.
-Those are all sauces.

261
00:11:33,726 --> 00:11:35,961
-He has so many of those.
-Spicy sauces.

262
00:11:36,028 --> 00:11:39,198
-These come in all kinds of sizes.
-The sauce.

263
00:11:39,265 --> 00:11:40,700
That's just what I like!

264
00:11:42,501 --> 00:11:44,303
The chefs look torn.

265
00:11:44,370 --> 00:11:48,974
Chef Yusuke lifted his glasses
to take another look.

266
00:11:49,041 --> 00:11:50,176
Do you use all these?

267
00:11:50,242 --> 00:11:51,644
-At home?
-Yes.

268
00:11:51,711 --> 00:11:53,179
Are you a spicy food guy?

269
00:11:53,245 --> 00:11:54,847
Yes, I enjoy spicy food very much.

270
00:11:54,914 --> 00:11:56,348
I've probably been to every place

271
00:11:56,415 --> 00:11:58,050
that served famous spicy dishes in Korea.

272
00:11:58,117 --> 00:12:01,087
-I see the word "death" on these.
-Death?

273
00:12:01,153 --> 00:12:04,590
The blue death sauce is really spicy.

274
00:12:05,157 --> 00:12:06,292
SCARED

275
00:12:06,358 --> 00:12:07,860
You must love spicy food.

276
00:12:07,927 --> 00:12:10,162
There is one sauce
that's the most dangerous.

277
00:12:10,229 --> 00:12:11,263
-Can you guess?
-A dangerous sauce.

278
00:12:11,330 --> 00:12:14,433
-The smallest one on the bottom shelf.
-This one?

279
00:12:14,500 --> 00:12:17,303
-This one?
-It's tiny, so it looks even spicier.

280
00:12:17,369 --> 00:12:19,004
-It looks strong.
-It's even scarier.

281
00:12:19,071 --> 00:12:22,441
-It's probably 600,000 Scoville Heat Unit.
-What?

282
00:12:22,508 --> 00:12:26,846
There's a warning.
The bottle shows a warning.

283
00:12:26,912 --> 00:12:28,114
Keun-suk, do you know what this is?

284
00:12:28,180 --> 00:12:30,883
-I've never seen it before.
-Habanero sauce?

285
00:12:30,950 --> 00:12:32,752
May I try that?

286
00:12:32,818 --> 00:12:34,220
-Would you like to?
-Try this?

287
00:12:34,286 --> 00:12:36,956
Who's better at taking spicy food?

288
00:12:37,022 --> 00:12:39,992
There are people who enjoy spicy food,

289
00:12:40,059 --> 00:12:42,161
