who don't feel the spiciness.

290
00:12:42,228 --> 00:12:44,597
-Wait.
-They're on different levels.

291
00:12:44,663 --> 00:12:48,134
He wants to enjoy it,
but he can't feel the spiciness at all.

292
00:12:48,200 --> 00:12:49,869
He doesn't know what spiciness is like.

293
00:12:50,970 --> 00:12:55,241
-It looks like lava.
-Keun-suk has never found anything spicy.

294
00:12:55,307 --> 00:12:57,042
He took a big dip.

295
00:12:57,109 --> 00:12:59,945
That level of spiciness is

296
00:13:00,012 --> 00:13:02,314
something Jae-joong finds spicy.

297
00:13:02,381 --> 00:13:03,916
-That's what he thinks is spicy.
-Yes.

298
00:13:03,983 --> 00:13:04,917
I see.

299
00:13:04,984 --> 00:13:05,985
-What?
-"I see."

300
00:13:06,051 --> 00:13:08,921
-Wait a second.
-It must be spicy!

301
00:13:10,256 --> 00:13:11,257
I see.

302
00:13:11,323 --> 00:13:13,626
HE SOUNDS DIFFERENT

303
00:13:13,692 --> 00:13:17,329
-It must be spicy!
-Wait a second. It must feel spicy.

304
00:13:17,396 --> 00:13:19,198
It must feel spicy.

305
00:13:19,265 --> 00:13:21,333
Your face is turning red.

306
00:13:21,400 --> 00:13:23,636
-Your ears are about to explode.
-No.

307
00:13:23,702 --> 00:13:25,304
-Wait a moment.
-He uses this to cook.

308
00:13:25,371 --> 00:13:27,273
Hey, look at Keun-suk.

309
00:13:27,339 --> 00:13:30,176
I think he can feel it now.

310
00:13:30,242 --> 00:13:32,545
-Didn't it taste spicy?
-No, not at all.

311
00:13:32,611 --> 00:13:34,079
Why did you suddenly do this?

312
00:13:34,146 --> 00:13:35,247
The lights were too bright.

313
00:13:37,950 --> 00:13:39,084
-Okay.
-Not bad.

314
00:13:39,151 --> 00:13:41,987
THE ONES WHO WERE
CAPTIVATED BY CURIOSITY

315
00:13:48,294 --> 00:13:50,062
Here's what it feels like.

316
00:13:53,332 --> 00:13:54,333
COUGH

317
00:13:56,001 --> 00:13:58,237
It just hurts.

318
00:13:58,938 --> 00:14:01,473
-It hits you later and stays longer.
-It stays longer.

319
00:14:02,842 --> 00:14:05,744
-This is crazy.
-I almost had hiccups.

320
00:14:05,811 --> 00:14:08,347
I have one question. How do you use this?

321
00:14:08,414 --> 00:14:11,450
-What do you use it for?
-I use it to make bibimbap.

322
00:14:11,517 --> 00:14:13,319
You use this as bibimbap sauce?

323
00:14:13,385 --> 00:14:15,354
-Bibimbap?
-How much do you use?

324
00:14:15,421 --> 00:14:17,122
-How much do you use?
-Yes, how much?

325
00:14:17,189 --> 00:14:18,591
Three times as much as this.

326
00:14:18,657 --> 00:14:20,726
It'll make the sauce very spicy.

327
00:14:20,793 --> 00:14:22,461
I have a question.

328
00:14:22,528 --> 00:14:24,296
-This is crazy.
-Do you feel okay in the restroom?

329
00:14:24,363 --> 00:14:25,698
Oh, here's the thing.

330
00:14:25,764 --> 00:14:28,667
I've been an idol star for 23 years,

331
00:14:28,734 --> 00:14:30,703
so I began to go to the restroom
starting two years ago.

332
00:14:31,270 --> 00:14:32,638
THE IDOL STAR OF MANY YEARS IS
QUITE HEALTHY

333
00:14:32,705 --> 00:14:35,174
-I know what that's like.
-You began to go only recently?

334
00:14:35,241 --> 00:14:37,176
-I started last year.
-Last year?

335
00:14:37,910 --> 00:14:39,545
You can join the showoffs.

336
00:14:39,612 --> 00:14:41,347
A SPECIAL PERMISSION
TO JOIN THE SHOWOFFS

337
00:14:41,413 --> 00:14:43,482
-I'm sweating.
-That was spicy.

338
00:14:43,549 --> 00:14:45,751
The top shelf is all Korean food.

339
00:14:45,818 --> 00:14:48,954
-<i>Doenjang</i>. Lots of paste sauces.
-He has lots of pastes.

340
00:14:49,021 --> 00:14:52,524
-That must be <i>mak-doenjang</i>.
-This must be the traditional type.

341
00:14:52,591 --> 00:14:53,959
Yes, it's homemade.

342
00:14:54,026 --> 00:14:56,729
-Who made it? Your mom?
-My mom.

343
00:14:56,795 --> 00:14:59,198
-What about this? <i>Ssamjang</i>?
-My mom made that too.

344
00:14:59,265 --> 00:15:00,566
Homemade <i>ssamjang</i>.

345
00:15:00,633 --> 00:15:04,069
He has lots of homemade ingredients.
They're not store-bought.

346
00:15:04,136 --> 00:15:05,337
This is gochujang.

347
00:15:05,404 --> 00:15:06,906
The top shelf.

348
00:15:06,972 --> 00:15:10,109
Have you ever heard
of the three Korean paste sauces?

349
00:15:10,175 --> 00:15:12,978
-Gochujang and <i>doenjang</i>.
-Gochujang, yes.

350
00:15:13,045 --> 00:15:16,215
-If you mix the two, it becomes <i>ssamjang</i>.
-So it's a mix.

351
00:15:16,282 --> 00:15:19,685
-Do you cook often at home?
-Yes, I do.

352
00:15:19,752 --> 00:15:23,088
When I go over
to Jae-joong's place to eat,

353
00:15:23,155 --> 00:15:25,291
I've never had any delivery food.

354
00:15:25,357 --> 00:15:27,026
-I see.
-Come to think of it, it was so.

355
00:15:27,092 --> 00:15:30,129
It was faster to whip up something
than to wait for the delivery to come.

356
00:15:31,397 --> 00:15:32,498
-What?
-He's the cooking type.

357
00:15:32,564 --> 00:15:35,200
I can quickly make something
in 15 minutes.

358
00:15:36,135 --> 00:15:37,403
Will you be here next week?

359
00:15:37,970 --> 00:15:40,205
THE PRIDE FOR HIS COOKING SKILLS
SEEMS FAMILIAR

360
00:15:40,272 --> 00:15:42,241
-It sounds familiar.
-We will…

361
00:15:42,308 --> 00:15:44,076
watch what Keun-suk does today,

362
00:15:44,143 --> 00:15:47,012
and if it looks like he won't give us
enough time on air, we'll switch.

363
00:15:47,079 --> 00:15:48,213
Is this kimchi?

364
00:15:48,280 --> 00:15:50,849
-Yes, that's kimchi.
-Oh, kimchi.

365
00:15:50,916 --> 00:15:52,217
-Gosh.
-It's napa cabbage kimchi.

366
00:15:52,284 --> 00:15:55,888
-There are so many kinds.
-I have many different kinds.

367
00:15:55,955 --> 00:15:58,057
-Is that salted seafood?
-It is.

368
00:15:58,123 --> 00:16:00,459
-Pollack roes.
-Salted seafood.

369
00:16:00,526 --> 00:16:01,794
Perilla leaves.

370
00:16:01,860 --> 00:16:04,763
-And quail eggs.
-Perilla leaves look good.

371
00:16:04,830 --> 00:16:06,832
He doesn't have anything like cheese.

372
00:16:06,899 --> 00:16:08,634
-He doesn't.
-There are no Western ingredients.

373
00:16:08,701 --> 00:16:12,304
-I'm the local cuisine kind of guy.
-You must only love Korean food.

374
00:16:12,371 --> 00:16:13,372
Yes, completely.

375
00:16:13,439 --> 00:16:14,840
What's this?

376
00:16:14,907 --> 00:16:16,442
-Stir-fried mushrooms.
-Stir-fried mushrooms.

377
00:16:16,508 --> 00:16:18,844
I made that with those.

378
00:16:18,911 --> 00:16:21,580
Those turned into this
after you grew them?

379
00:16:21,647 --> 00:16:23,582
-So it really works?
-You must like mushrooms.

380
00:16:23,649 --> 00:16:25,117
I do.

381
00:16:25,184 --> 00:16:26,618
And the fresh produce.

382
00:16:26,685 --> 00:16:30,022
-Mushrooms. He must enjoy the texture.
-There are lots.

383
00:16:30,089 --> 00:16:32,958
If I had to choose between a country
that only eats meat or vegetables,

384
00:16:33,025 --> 00:16:35,995
I'd probably choose
the side that only eats vegetables.

385
00:16:36,061 --> 00:16:39,365
I prefer vegetables over meat.

386
00:16:39,431 --> 00:16:40,766
-I see.
-He has many different kinds.

387
00:16:40,833 --> 00:16:42,201
-Radish.
-Yes.

388
00:16:42,267 --> 00:16:44,737
These are
the usual vegetables we all know.

389
00:16:44,803 --> 00:16:48,474
-He also has bottles of <i>makgeolli</i>.
-You must like <i>makgeolli</i>.

390
00:16:48,540 --> 00:16:50,242
Yes, because I mostly enjoy Korean food.

391
00:16:50,309 --> 00:16:52,811
The one in the far right is

392
00:16:52,878 --> 00:16:54,713
the <i>makgeolli </i>I made.

393
00:16:54,780 --> 00:16:56,815
-What? You made it?
-You made it yourself?

394
00:16:56,882 --> 00:16:59,785
You must like it so much if you made this.

395
00:16:59,852 --> 00:17:01,820
-Can we open a bottle?
-Yes, of course.

396
00:17:01,887 --> 00:17:03,789
He loves <i>makgeolli </i>very much.

397
00:17:03,856 --> 00:17:06,158
-Chefs, please try some.
-It's sweet.

398
00:17:06,225 --> 00:17:08,727
