407
00:17:24,510 --> 00:17:25,878
I thought he'd say, "<i>Oishii</i>."

408
00:17:25,944 --> 00:17:27,646
-It's good.
-It's good.

409
00:17:27,713 --> 00:17:28,714
Chef Li Guang?

410
00:17:28,781 --> 00:17:32,351
Very good.
It tastes like banana and caramel.

411
00:17:32,418 --> 00:17:35,888
Not too sweet,
but it's very easy to drink.

412
00:17:35,954 --> 00:17:37,623
Let's move on to the freezer.

413
00:17:37,689 --> 00:17:38,957
Gosh, squids.

414
00:17:39,024 --> 00:17:41,760
-He has lots of squids.
-He does. There are a few over there.

415
00:17:41,827 --> 00:17:44,596
I found blue crabs and abalones.

416
00:17:44,663 --> 00:17:45,931
Do you enjoy seafood?

417
00:17:45,998 --> 00:17:48,834
-Squid is my favorite.
-Squid is his favorite.

418
00:17:48,901 --> 00:17:51,470
You have to listen up. He loves squid.

419
00:17:51,537 --> 00:17:54,006
It's good when it's raw, when it's boiled,

420
00:17:54,073 --> 00:17:56,475
