462
00:19:38,677 --> 00:19:42,214
and even their opponent.

463
00:19:42,281 --> 00:19:45,450
Now, the spicy food. The spiciest.

464
00:19:45,517 --> 00:19:47,753
The spiciest food, anyone?

465
00:19:48,987 --> 00:19:49,988
It's so obvious.

466
00:19:50,055 --> 00:19:52,457
RAISING HAND

467
00:19:52,524 --> 00:19:53,959
-Keun-suk.
-I knew it.

468
00:19:54,026 --> 00:19:57,496
I'll make Asia's spiciest dish.

469
00:19:57,563 --> 00:19:59,598
AS EXPECTED

470
00:19:59,665 --> 00:20:00,666
And who's your opponent?

471
00:20:00,732 --> 00:20:03,569
-I'd like to choose Poong.
-Webtoon Artist Poong.

472
00:20:03,635 --> 00:20:08,307
Keun-suk and Poong will fight
to make Asia's spiciest dish.

473
00:20:08,373 --> 00:20:09,841
And next, Do You Know Makgeolli?

474
00:20:09,908 --> 00:20:11,376
RAISING HAND

475
00:20:12,077 --> 00:20:16,615
I like <i>makgeolli</i>,
so I want to pair a dish with that.

476
00:20:16,682 --> 00:20:18,083
Who would you like to fight?

477
00:20:18,150 --> 00:20:21,220
I want to cook
with the chef with most stars.

478
00:20:21,286 --> 00:20:24,056
My Korean brother, Chef Hyun-suk.

479
00:20:24,122 --> 00:20:25,290
WHOA

480
00:20:25,357 --> 00:20:26,792
The Han Li Guang of Korea.

481
00:20:26,858 --> 00:20:30,362
-The Han Li Guang of Korea?
-The Han Li Guang of Korea.

482
00:20:30,429 --> 00:20:32,164
We decided on the contestants.

483
00:20:32,231 --> 00:20:35,567
Let the 15-minute cook-offs begin!

484
00:20:39,238 --> 00:20:40,272
Go!

485
00:20:40,339 --> 00:20:43,775
<i>Chef & My Fridge,</i>
<i>slowly becoming a global show.</i>

486
00:20:43,842 --> 00:20:45,611
<i>You're now watching</i>
<i>the Big Asian Competition.</i>

487
00:20:45,677 --> 00:20:47,913
<i>We're about to begin</i>
<i>the long-awaited opening round.</i>

488
00:20:47,980 --> 00:20:51,316
Jang Keun-suk, the Asian cook
who makes knockout dishes,

489
00:20:51,383 --> 00:20:55,954
and the knockoff chef of <i>Chef & My Fridge,</i>
Webtoon Artist Kim Poong.

490
00:20:56,021 --> 00:20:58,924
Poong, do you believe you're
a suitable candidate for the opening game?

491
00:20:59,558 --> 00:21:01,793
Well, I'm not made for the final round.

492
00:21:02,761 --> 00:21:04,162
-That's true.
-That's right.

493
00:21:04,229 --> 00:21:06,231
-You can't make it that far.
-No.

494
00:21:06,298 --> 00:21:09,601
This is quite important,
as this is the opening game.

495
00:21:09,668 --> 00:21:12,371
Which team will take the first victory?

496
00:21:12,437 --> 00:21:13,972
I'm quite nervous.

497
00:21:14,039 --> 00:21:17,242
When I watched the show on TV,
I thought 15 minutes should be

498
00:21:17,309 --> 00:21:19,645
-more than enough.
-Yes?

499
00:21:19,711 --> 00:21:21,013
But now that I stand here,

500
00:21:21,079 --> 00:21:23,749
I feel sick, nauseated, and dizzy.

501
00:21:23,815 --> 00:21:24,983
You're biting your lips.

502
00:21:25,550 --> 00:21:26,785
ANXIOUS AND FRETFUL

503
00:21:26,852 --> 00:21:28,954
I've never seen you get nervous.

504
00:21:29,021 --> 00:21:31,456
You seem a bit nervous today.

505
00:21:31,523 --> 00:21:33,558
I have no idea why I'm here.

506
00:21:33,625 --> 00:21:36,762
Where did your bluffs go?
I've never seen you like this.

507
00:21:36,828 --> 00:21:39,831
Chef Jong-won said something like
this to our production crew.

508
00:21:39,898 --> 00:21:42,267
"Even if the 1st place
of Asia's 50 Best Restaurants come,

509
00:21:42,334 --> 00:21:44,836
there's a possibility Poong may win."

510
00:21:45,537 --> 00:21:47,572
THE 25TH PLACE AND NAM-NO ARE
MESMERIZED BY POONG

511
00:21:47,639 --> 00:21:50,342
He's right. You never know.

512
00:21:51,143 --> 00:21:53,445
I'm about to cry.

513
00:21:54,346 --> 00:21:56,848
He was moved. He was moved to tears.

514
00:21:57,416 --> 00:22:01,019
-Why is that so?
-People think he'd be easy to beat,

515
00:22:01,086 --> 00:22:03,155
but you might end up losing.

516
00:22:03,221 --> 00:22:07,826
Poong has a certain kind of magical charm.

517
00:22:07,893 --> 00:22:09,094
As you've already tried,

518
00:22:09,161 --> 00:22:11,263
his dishes are
much more delicious than you expect.

519
00:22:11,330 --> 00:22:13,265
-You should be ready.
-Yes.

520
00:22:13,332 --> 00:22:16,134
Chef Li Guang looks anxious.

521
00:22:16,201 --> 00:22:18,470
You should be glad
you aren't fighting Poong today.

522
00:22:18,537 --> 00:22:21,039
-Today…
-I'm sorry, but can we begin already?

523
00:22:21,106 --> 00:22:23,775
I'm dizzy. I have a headache.

524
00:22:23,842 --> 00:22:28,347
We provide a perk for the chefs
who are here for the first time.

525
00:22:28,413 --> 00:22:29,581
Right, the perk.

526
00:22:29,648 --> 00:22:31,650
You may choose one of the three.

527
00:22:31,717 --> 00:22:34,319
Men are supposed to fight fair and square,

528
00:22:34,386 --> 00:22:36,088
so I'll stop him for a minute.

529
00:22:38,690 --> 00:22:40,726
YES, THEY'RE ON POONG'S TEAM

530
00:22:40,792 --> 00:22:43,228
-Didn't you like to bluff?
-Jeez.

531
00:22:43,295 --> 00:22:45,330
Where are your bluffs?

532
00:22:45,397 --> 00:22:47,866
-Stop for one minute!
-All right.

533
00:22:47,933 --> 00:22:49,601
Stopping for one minute.

534
00:22:50,535 --> 00:22:52,704
KEUN-SUK'S INGREDIENTS: LEMON, SHRIMP,
CHILI GARLIC PASTE, SPICY PEPPER POWDER

535
00:22:52,771 --> 00:22:54,940
CHEONGYANG PEPPER POWDER, CROWN DAISY,
CURRY POWDER, MANILA CLAM, AND MORE

536
00:22:55,006 --> 00:22:57,776
I'm going to make a dish called

537
00:22:57,843 --> 00:22:59,277
Surreally Spicy.

538
00:22:59,344 --> 00:23:02,547
-Surreally Spicy.
-Surreally Spicy.

539
00:23:02,614 --> 00:23:05,984
Today's guest, Jae-joong, has this image.

540
00:23:06,051 --> 00:23:10,956
He's almost surreally good-looking,
so we say he's right out of a comic book.

541
00:23:11,022 --> 00:23:12,858
But not only that,

542
00:23:12,924 --> 00:23:15,060
he has a big twist

543
00:23:15,127 --> 00:23:18,630
in his appetite for hardcore
spicy food like a manly man.

544
00:23:18,697 --> 00:23:20,932
So I wanted to call this Surreally Spicy,
just like his surreal looks.

545
00:23:22,434 --> 00:23:24,169
My goal today is

546
00:23:24,236 --> 00:23:27,172
make a surreally spicy dish,

547
00:23:27,239 --> 00:23:30,075
get my surreally overwhelming win
against Poong,

548
00:23:30,142 --> 00:23:32,144
and destroy the show almost surreally.

549
00:23:33,545 --> 00:23:34,546
I see.

550
00:23:34,613 --> 00:23:36,515
HIS BLUFFING IS BACK

551
00:23:36,581 --> 00:23:38,016
FLAPPING

552
00:23:38,083 --> 00:23:40,819
OH, MY CAPTAIN

553
00:23:40,886 --> 00:23:42,621
-He's a showoff.
-I knew it.

554
00:23:42,687 --> 00:23:45,457
-His showtime is back.
-It's showtime!

555
00:23:46,825 --> 00:23:48,994
I saw that you were using seafood.

556
00:23:49,060 --> 00:23:51,730
I'm going to make paella

557
00:23:51,797 --> 00:23:54,833
with instant rice
and seafood as the base flavor.

558
00:23:54,900 --> 00:23:56,334
-Paella?
-Paella?

559
00:23:56,401 --> 00:23:58,770
-Paella?
-Yes, the Spanish dish.

560
00:23:58,837 --> 00:24:00,705
-Can he do it in 15 minutes?
-Do you have enough time?

561
00:24:00,772 --> 00:24:02,674
It takes a long time to make it.

562
00:24:02,741 --> 00:24:05,677
I'll cut down the time
by using instant rice.

563
00:24:05,744 --> 00:24:10,215
-I see. He already has a plan.
-He planned it out.

564
00:24:11,149 --> 00:24:13,318
POONG'S INGREDIENTS: BHUT JOLOKIA SAUCE,
LIQUID CHEONG PEPPER SAUCE, RADISH

565
00:24:13,385 --> 00:24:15,554
LETTUCE, PERILLA LEAF, MALA POWDER,
SQUID, ANCHOVY SAUCE, HOT SAUCE, AND MORE

566
00:24:15,620 --> 00:24:17,389
The dish I'll make is called

567
00:24:17,456 --> 00:24:21,259
Hottes-quid in Asia.

568
00:24:21,326 --> 00:24:25,797
-I see. Hottes-quid in Asia.
-Hottes-quid in Asia.

569
00:24:25,864 --> 00:24:26,898
What's this like?

570
00:24:26,965 --> 00:24:29,334
He said he loved squid the most.

571
00:24:29,401 --> 00:24:31,837
Have you had Sokcho-style squid <i>bossam</i>?

572
00:24:31,903 --> 00:24:33,438
-Yes.
-Yes, right?

573
00:24:33,505 --> 00:24:37,976
I'll reinterpret that dish
in Poong's style

574
00:24:38,043 --> 00:24:39,744
and bring out different textures.

575
00:24:39,811 --> 00:24:42,080
I'll drop all my ethics

576
00:24:42,147 --> 00:24:44,883
and make something damningly spicy.

577
00:24:44,950 --> 00:24:47,719
You're watching the Big Asian Competition.

578
00:24:47,786 --> 00:24:50,322
Let us begin the opening game.

579
00:24:50,388 --> 00:24:52,557
Damn it. What the heck is this?

580
00:24:52,624 --> 00:24:55,227
-Gosh.
-You can do it!

581
00:24:55,994 --> 00:24:57,662
ARGH

582
00:24:58,330 --> 00:25:00,365
THE RETURNING CHEF IS
FULLY RECHARGED WITH LUNACY

583
00:25:00,432 --> 00:25:02,534
Jang Keun-suk!

584
00:25:04,503 --> 00:25:06,438
Settle down.

585
00:25:06,505 --> 00:25:09,674
He's here to take
his surreally overwhelming win

586
00:25:09,741 --> 00:25:11,443
with his unethically spicy dish.

587
00:25:11,510 --> 00:25:14,179
The knockout cook of Asia, Jang Keun-suk.

588
00:25:14,246 --> 00:25:17,616
But this man is here today
to break all human ethics.

589
00:25:17,682 --> 00:25:20,919
The knockoff chef of <i>Chef & My</i>
<i>Fridge</i>, Kim Poong is up.

590
00:25:20,986 --> 00:25:23,221
This is the opening game
of the Big Asian Competition.

591
00:25:23,288 --> 00:25:26,725
Which one of them will seize the victory?

592
00:25:26,791 --> 00:25:27,859
Let's begin!

593
00:25:31,229 --> 00:25:32,330
You both got this!

594
00:25:32,397 --> 00:25:34,366
He begins by preparing squid.

595
00:25:34,432 --> 00:25:36,902
Both sides are using squids.

596
00:25:36,968 --> 00:25:41,406
Let's see how good Keun-suk is
at using a knife.

597
00:25:41,473 --> 00:25:43,241
-He's good.
-He is.

598
00:25:43,308 --> 00:25:45,911
Keun-suk isn't so bad.

599
00:25:45,977 --> 00:25:49,080
-He said he liked that part.
-Yes, that part.

600
00:25:49,147 --> 00:25:51,383
I need him to chop up the long tentacles.

601
00:25:51,449 --> 00:25:53,218
-The long ones?
-Chop it in half.

602
00:25:53,285 --> 00:25:55,153
He wants you to chop them. Good.

603
00:25:55,220 --> 00:25:57,689
He's sensitive about the texture.

604
00:25:57,756 --> 00:26:00,525
He must be making a good portion.

605
00:26:00,592 --> 00:26:02,894
Poong begins with radish.

606
00:26:02,961 --> 00:26:05,030
-The sliced radish is important.
-Sliced radish?

607
00:26:05,096 --> 00:26:07,899
Sliced radish is the key
to Sokcho-style stir-fried squid.

608
00:26:07,966 --> 00:26:09,467
Are you putting in radish?

609
00:26:09,534 --> 00:26:13,338
The radish will
get rid of the fishy squid smell.

610
00:26:13,905 --> 00:26:15,941
HE CUTS UP A FEW MORE PIECES

611
00:26:16,675 --> 00:26:18,843
-They weren't cut.
-It's fine.

612
00:26:19,411 --> 00:26:20,512
HE RIPPED THEM APART

613
00:26:21,146 --> 00:26:22,981
DROPPING SALT

614
00:26:23,048 --> 00:26:24,916
What's that? Salt?

615
00:26:24,983 --> 00:26:26,017
Salt?

616
00:26:26,084 --> 00:26:29,988
Poong works on radish salad
as soon as he begins.

617
00:26:30,055 --> 00:26:31,056
He's bringing out the texture.

618
00:26:31,122 --> 00:26:33,692
He salted it to get rid of its water.

619
00:26:33,758 --> 00:26:36,861
-I think he's trying to make them firmer.
-Bingo.

620
00:26:36,928 --> 00:26:39,097
Nam-no is a smart one.

621
00:26:39,664 --> 00:26:41,066
KEUN-SUK PULLS OUT AN ONION

622
00:26:41,633 --> 00:26:43,668
VERTICALLY

623
00:26:43,735 --> 00:26:46,972
HORIZONTALLY

624
00:26:47,672 --> 00:26:49,107
AND AGAIN, VERTICALLY

625
00:26:49,174 --> 00:26:52,510
He knows the basics of chopping.

626
00:26:53,244 --> 00:26:56,281
HE CRUSHES
THE GARLIC CLOVES FIRST

627
00:26:57,549 --> 00:27:00,719
-Keun-suk is quite good with the knife.
-He's good.

628
00:27:00,785 --> 00:27:03,321
-He's done this a lot.
-He's good with it.

629
00:27:03,388 --> 00:27:07,192
-Keun-suk is much better.
-Sung-hoon can see it too.

630
00:27:08,026 --> 00:27:10,595
Keun-suk is a bit better with the knife.

631
00:27:10,662 --> 00:27:11,896
The thing is,

632
00:27:11,963 --> 00:27:15,467
he seems shaky when he cooks,
just like drunken boxing.

633
00:27:15,533 --> 00:27:17,936
But he'll attack you
when you let your guard down.

634
00:27:18,003 --> 00:27:21,740
Keun-suk is fighting in the tai chi style.

635
00:27:21,806 --> 00:27:23,475
He's the drunken boxer,
and he does tai chi.

636
00:27:23,541 --> 00:27:25,243
Yes, right.

637
00:27:25,310 --> 00:27:28,446
Keun-suk is calmer.
He's calmer than I expected.

638
00:27:28,513 --> 00:27:31,483
-He's stir-frying Manila clams.
-Are those Manila clams?

639
00:27:31,549 --> 00:27:33,685
I'm frying Manila clams and squid.

640
00:27:33,752 --> 00:27:35,286
-Are you cooking them together?
-Yes.

641
00:27:35,353 --> 00:27:39,691
-He's making seafood broth.
-Seafood broth.

642
00:27:39,758 --> 00:27:42,160
-He begins to parboil bean sprouts.
-Are you parboiling those?

643
00:27:42,227 --> 00:27:43,361
I'm making bean sprout soup.

644
00:27:43,428 --> 00:27:45,997
Look at how Poong is moving
like a drunken boxer.

645
00:27:46,898 --> 00:27:47,999
What's that?

646
00:27:48,066 --> 00:27:49,534
-Vinegar.
-To get rid of the smell.

647
00:27:49,601 --> 00:27:51,703
-The grassy smell.
-The bean smell.

648
00:27:51,770 --> 00:27:53,505
-Is that a good method?
-Yes, it is.

649
00:27:53,571 --> 00:27:57,809
Some people boil bean sprouts
without covering it up because of that.

650
00:27:57,876 --> 00:27:59,911
-That's a good idea.
-I knew it.

651
00:27:59,978 --> 00:28:01,579
Is that soy sauce?

652
00:28:01,646 --> 00:28:04,115
-Anchovy sauce.
-That's not a bad idea.

653
00:28:05,316 --> 00:28:06,885
He's making soup.

654
00:28:06,951 --> 00:28:07,986
That's MSG.

655
00:28:08,053 --> 00:28:10,955
-MSG? I thought it was salt.
-He's using MSG out in the open.

656
00:28:11,523 --> 00:28:13,892
POURING IN BEEF STOCK

657
00:28:15,860 --> 00:28:17,929
Wouldn't it be better to make ramyeon?

658
00:28:18,496 --> 00:28:20,598
HIS TECHNIQUES
ARE OUT OF THIS WORLD

659
00:28:20,665 --> 00:28:22,033
-Nine minutes left.
-Nine minutes.

660
00:28:22,100 --> 00:28:23,535
-Jeez. Already?
-Nine minutes.

661
00:28:23,601 --> 00:28:25,537
Keun-suk hasn't used the stopping perk.

662
00:28:25,603 --> 00:28:27,772
You should start on the paella.

663
00:28:27,839 --> 00:28:29,808
Finally, the spicy sauce.

664
00:28:29,874 --> 00:28:32,043
He's finally using the spicy ingredients.

665
00:28:32,110 --> 00:28:34,145
Keun-suk, did you warm up instant rice?

666
00:28:34,212 --> 00:28:35,914
No, I'll use it cold.

667
00:28:35,980 --> 00:28:37,148
You'll use it cold?

668
00:28:37,215 --> 00:28:39,551
It'll become hydrated when it's warm.

669
00:28:39,617 --> 00:28:42,454
So it'd be better
if the rice grains were harder.

670
00:28:43,455 --> 00:28:46,925
I haven't seen anyone using
extra spicy sauce so far.

671
00:28:46,991 --> 00:28:49,627
Right? These don't look so spicy.

672
00:28:50,361 --> 00:28:51,463
What was that?

673
00:28:51,529 --> 00:28:55,900
It's a mix of chili and garlic
flakes. It's like a paste.

674
00:28:55,967 --> 00:28:57,569
Yes, he had that back there.

675
00:28:57,635 --> 00:28:59,504
He had all kinds of sauces.

676
00:29:00,071 --> 00:29:01,873
SAMBAL SAUCE,
SPICY PEPPER POWDER

677
00:29:01,940 --> 00:29:04,309
-This is curry powder.
-Curry powder.

678
00:29:04,375 --> 00:29:06,311
Keun-suk suddenly adds curry powder.

679
00:29:06,377 --> 00:29:09,781
I didn't see any saffron,
so I'm using this instead.

680
00:29:09,848 --> 00:29:11,216
-I see.
-Saffron is a must for paella.

681
00:29:11,282 --> 00:29:13,885
-He has to give it that color.
-He didn't have it here.

682
00:29:13,952 --> 00:29:15,820
-He's using that instead.
-That's a clever idea.

683
00:29:15,887 --> 00:29:19,457
-That's a good idea.
-Keun-suk shows a great idea.

684
00:29:19,524 --> 00:29:21,526
I have a feeling

685
00:29:21,593 --> 00:29:24,162
Keun-suk may become a regular
instead of Poong if this goes well.

686
00:29:24,229 --> 00:29:27,298
Yes, well,
if that's what our viewers want.

687
00:29:27,365 --> 00:29:29,467
Hey, wait.

688
00:29:30,034 --> 00:29:31,836
POURING

689
00:29:31,903 --> 00:29:33,671
He emptied it out.

690
00:29:33,738 --> 00:29:36,407
-He emptied it out.
-What's that?

691
00:29:36,474 --> 00:29:38,409
It was Cheongyang pepper powder.

692
00:29:38,476 --> 00:29:40,145
-The green thing?
-Yes.

693
00:29:40,211 --> 00:29:41,546
He put in that much?

694
00:29:41,613 --> 00:29:43,348
He just dropped in two spicy sauces.

695
00:29:43,414 --> 00:29:45,550
And some minced garlic as well.

696
00:29:45,617 --> 00:29:48,686
-Anchovy sauce too.
-Beef stock and anchovy sauce.

697
00:29:48,753 --> 00:29:50,622
How will you use that, Poong?

698
00:29:50,688 --> 00:29:52,223
This is the marinade.

699
00:29:52,290 --> 00:29:53,758
-The marinade?
-That's the marinade?

700
00:29:53,825 --> 00:29:56,094
That's the marinade for squid <i>bossam</i>?

701
00:29:56,161 --> 00:29:57,829
It looks like wasabi.

702
00:29:57,896 --> 00:30:00,131
-Cheongyang pepper…
-It does.

703
00:30:01,266 --> 00:30:02,734
SPICINESS FROM THE OUTER WORLD

704
00:30:02,801 --> 00:30:05,603
This was what he meant
by something unethically spicy.

705
00:30:05,670 --> 00:30:07,539
Stop that, Poong.

706
00:30:07,605 --> 00:30:09,674
You'll end up hurting him.

707
00:30:09,741 --> 00:30:13,344
-I'd probably die if I tried that.
-Yes.

708
00:30:13,411 --> 00:30:15,914
I'd probably die as soon as I ate that.

709
00:30:15,980 --> 00:30:17,482
He's using the squid.

710
00:30:17,549 --> 00:30:19,350
Poong grabbed a squid too.

711
00:30:19,417 --> 00:30:22,687
Poong cut it vertically and flattened it.

712
00:30:22,754 --> 00:30:24,789
-Longways.
-I see.

713
00:30:24,856 --> 00:30:26,324
He's cutting it like noodles.

714
00:30:26,391 --> 00:30:28,459
Will it go into the bean sprout soup?

715
00:30:28,526 --> 00:30:31,896
-It's for the stir-fry. The <i>bossam</i>.
-I see.

716
00:30:31,963 --> 00:30:34,432
I think he'll stir-fry it in spicy sauce.

717
00:30:34,499 --> 00:30:35,500
Like <i>bossam</i>?

718
00:30:35,567 --> 00:30:38,336
Is he making two dishes?
The soup and <i>bossam</i>?

719
00:30:38,403 --> 00:30:41,906
He has 7 minutes and 30 seconds left,
but he hasn't started on rice for paella.

720
00:30:41,973 --> 00:30:43,675
-Rice!
-My gosh.

721
00:30:43,741 --> 00:30:46,211
-Rice! I have to warm up rice.
-My gosh.

722
00:30:46,277 --> 00:30:49,147
-Poong needs rice too.
-You surprised me.

723
00:30:49,214 --> 00:30:51,316
-Hey, you fool.
-Yes.

724
00:30:51,382 --> 00:30:53,151
-He almost forgot.
-Thank you.

725
00:30:53,218 --> 00:30:54,352
He has good ears.

726
00:30:54,419 --> 00:30:57,956
I have no idea
when I should stop him for a minute.

727
00:30:58,022 --> 00:30:59,224
Can you help me with that?

728
00:30:59,290 --> 00:31:01,059
You can't use it after ten minutes.

729
00:31:01,125 --> 00:31:04,295
You can't use it after ten minutes.
Use it before the clock turns to five.

730
00:31:04,362 --> 00:31:07,432
-Use it now.
-You can stop him now.

731
00:31:07,498 --> 00:31:09,901
-Will you use it now?
-Stop!

732
00:31:09,968 --> 00:31:11,269
SHAKING

733
00:31:11,336 --> 00:31:13,271
You can't take it off heat.

734
00:31:13,338 --> 00:31:15,940
I hope the squid doesn't get overcooked.

735
00:31:16,007 --> 00:31:18,710
You have to wait there for a minute.

736
00:31:18,776 --> 00:31:20,979
You're killing my arm!

737
00:31:21,045 --> 00:31:23,081
-Fifty seconds.
-He has to hold it up.

738
00:31:23,147 --> 00:31:25,617
Fifty seconds.
Keun-suk needs to move quickly.

739
00:31:25,683 --> 00:31:27,385
PAELLA SAUCE

740
00:31:27,452 --> 00:31:29,020
The squid will get hard.

741
00:31:29,087 --> 00:31:30,855
My arm hurts.

742
00:31:30,922 --> 00:31:32,857
-Forty seconds.
-My arm.

743
00:31:33,424 --> 00:31:34,659
CRYING

744
00:31:34,726 --> 00:31:37,829
-He used it in a great timing.
-It was excellent.

745
00:31:37,896 --> 00:31:40,665
-He can't put the pot down.
-He can't.

746
00:31:40,732 --> 00:31:41,733
Thirty seconds.

747
00:31:41,799 --> 00:31:44,168
-He's using instant rice.
-He just dropped rice.

748
00:31:44,235 --> 00:31:47,839
It may turn too sticky like porridge
if I warm it up.

749
00:31:47,906 --> 00:31:51,576
-I wanted to use it while it was hard.
-My arm hurts!

750
00:31:51,643 --> 00:31:53,344
A minute is longer than you think.

751
00:31:53,411 --> 00:31:55,213
-Gosh, this is bad.
-Ten seconds.

752
00:31:55,280 --> 00:31:57,815
-Eight. Seven.
-It's almost up.

753
00:31:57,882 --> 00:31:59,884
-Six. Five. Four.
-Six. Five. Four.

754
00:31:59,951 --> 00:32:03,254
-Three. Two. One.
-Three. Two. One. It's over.

755
00:32:03,821 --> 00:32:05,423
THE 1-MINUTE STOP PERK ENDS

756
00:32:05,490 --> 00:32:07,859
-Was the squid overcooked?
-It's all crooked.

757
00:32:07,926 --> 00:32:11,963
-He had to wait for a minute.
-That was a tough perk.

758
00:32:12,030 --> 00:32:14,432
He should've pulled it out
as soon as he parboiled it,

759
00:32:14,499 --> 00:32:17,602
-but he overcooked it for a minute.
-So it could be overcooked?

760
00:32:17,669 --> 00:32:20,371
It wasn't overcooked. I can do this.

761
00:32:20,438 --> 00:32:22,240
You have six minutes.

762
00:32:22,907 --> 00:32:25,176
KEUN-SUK USES CHEONGYANG
PEPPER POWDER

763
00:32:25,743 --> 00:32:29,080
THE POWDER
SPRINKLES DOWN LIKE SNOW

764
00:32:29,948 --> 00:32:32,884
AND HE USES
THE HOT SAUCE HE TRIED

765
00:32:32,951 --> 00:32:35,153
It's that spicy sauce!

766
00:32:35,219 --> 00:32:36,688
-Keun-suk uses the spicy sauce!
-That's a lot.

767
00:32:36,754 --> 00:32:38,456
It must be really spicy.

768
00:32:40,058 --> 00:32:41,793
HE WASHES
AND DRAINS THE RADISH SALAD

769
00:32:41,859 --> 00:32:45,863
-It may be too salty. Try some.
-Really?

770
00:32:47,131 --> 00:32:48,132
See? It's too salty.

771
00:32:49,400 --> 00:32:52,036
-See? It's too salty.
-Of course, it is.

772
00:32:52,603 --> 00:32:54,872
HE USED TOO MUCH SALT
AND MADE THE RADISH TOO SALTY

773
00:32:54,939 --> 00:32:58,543
I think the radish is too salty.
He made it too salty.

774
00:32:58,609 --> 00:33:00,211
Are you doing it over?

775
00:33:00,278 --> 00:33:01,546
He had put in too much salt.

776
00:33:01,612 --> 00:33:03,581
Did you put in too much salt before?

777
00:33:03,648 --> 00:33:06,017
-He added like 100 g.
-He makes the radish salad again.

778
00:33:06,084 --> 00:33:07,318
Of course, it's salty.

779
00:33:07,385 --> 00:33:09,787
You should put in more radish.

780
00:33:09,854 --> 00:33:11,889
-This is bad.
-Can't you use those?

781
00:33:11,956 --> 00:33:13,825
No, it's unsalvageable.

782
00:33:13,891 --> 00:33:16,260
-He has no time to redo it, though.
-No.

783
00:33:16,327 --> 00:33:17,795
WILL HE SAVE
THE PRIDE OF THE SHOW?

784
00:33:17,862 --> 00:33:20,565
-Sung-ju, tell us about the situation.
-Yes?

785
00:33:20,631 --> 00:33:22,667
-Let me go out.
-Okay.

786
00:33:22,734 --> 00:33:24,469
Let me go out there.

787
00:33:24,535 --> 00:33:27,038
Look at that. Poong's green sauce.

788
00:33:27,105 --> 00:33:30,274
-The green sauce.
-The Cheongyang pepper powder.

789
00:33:30,341 --> 00:33:32,844
Can you try that?

790
00:33:32,910 --> 00:33:36,647
-This one looks frightening.
-It's scary.

791
00:33:38,149 --> 00:33:39,751
ROARS

792
00:33:39,817 --> 00:33:41,252
THE DRAGON SHOOTS OUT FIRE

793
00:33:41,319 --> 00:33:44,589
He put this sauce in here.

794
00:33:45,456 --> 00:33:48,026
All right. Wait.
Did you say this was salty?

795
00:33:48,092 --> 00:33:50,261
Let me check and see
if you should do this over.

796
00:33:52,096 --> 00:33:53,798
HOWLS

797
00:33:54,632 --> 00:33:55,800
TEARS

798
00:33:57,502 --> 00:33:58,903
Do it over. Throw this out.

799
00:33:59,971 --> 00:34:02,407
-You have to do it over.
-Yes, throw it out.

800
00:34:02,473 --> 00:34:03,875
How did you do that?

801
00:34:03,941 --> 00:34:06,811
-Of course, it's too salty.
-You need to redo that.

802
00:34:06,878 --> 00:34:08,279
LAUGHING

803
00:34:08,346 --> 00:34:10,348
-Hey, wait.
-It was too salty.

804
00:34:10,415 --> 00:34:11,816
Can you taste that?

805
00:34:11,883 --> 00:34:13,184
And Keun-suk.

806
00:34:13,251 --> 00:34:16,320
He put this sauce in here.

807
00:34:16,387 --> 00:34:20,224
-Everything is in there.
-And he put in Manila clams.

808
00:34:20,291 --> 00:34:23,361
Gosh, the spiciness is…

809
00:34:23,428 --> 00:34:26,764
KEUN-SUK'S SHOWTIME

810
00:34:26,831 --> 00:34:29,100
Look at his technique.

811
00:34:29,167 --> 00:34:30,401
It's spicy.

812
00:34:30,468 --> 00:34:33,071
-No, it's not spicy.
-Okay.

813
00:34:33,137 --> 00:34:35,072
Keun-suk's dish looks delicious.

814
00:34:35,139 --> 00:34:36,307
Keun-suk's dish.

815
00:34:36,374 --> 00:34:39,177
-We have 3 minutes and 20 seconds. Paella.
-The paella.

816
00:34:39,243 --> 00:34:41,312
Let me try the paella.

817
00:34:41,379 --> 00:34:42,814
Great job, Keun-suk.

818
00:34:42,880 --> 00:34:46,050
Is it surreally spicy?
Or is it just surreal?

819
00:34:46,117 --> 00:34:48,586
Is it surreally spicy?
Or is it just surreal?

820
00:34:49,520 --> 00:34:51,456
-Gah!
-Is it surreally spicy?

821
00:34:51,522 --> 00:34:53,124
He's tortured.

822
00:34:53,991 --> 00:34:56,394
I feel like dying, but I can handle this.

823
00:34:56,461 --> 00:34:59,097
-I doubt it's spicy enough for Jae-joong.
-It needs to be spicier.

824
00:34:59,163 --> 00:35:00,164
I can handle this.

825
00:35:01,432 --> 00:35:04,368
-He's serving the paella.
-I can deal with this.

826
00:35:04,435 --> 00:35:07,438
-It looks like paella.
-He knows what the real deal is like.

827
00:35:07,505 --> 00:35:10,408
-The paella looks good.
-Keun-suk is good at this.

828
00:35:10,975 --> 00:35:12,810
HOWEVER, THE KNOCKOFF CHEF IS
HAVING TROUBLE

829
00:35:12,877 --> 00:35:15,913
-Nothing smells spicy.
-No, it does.

830
