831
00:35:18,783 --> 00:35:20,284
What's this, Poong?

832
00:35:20,351 --> 00:35:21,652
This will become the squid <i>bossam</i>.

833
00:35:21,719 --> 00:35:23,187
-The squid <i>bossam</i>?
-Yes.

834
00:35:23,254 --> 00:35:26,023
You threw in
both squid and chopped radish.

835
00:35:26,090 --> 00:35:27,158
It doesn't seem right.

836
00:35:27,225 --> 00:35:29,827
Why does it look like that again?

837
00:35:29,894 --> 00:35:32,964
-I don't appreciate the color.
-I know. Actually,

838
00:35:33,030 --> 00:35:34,966
red isn't the real scary color.

839
00:35:36,134 --> 00:35:40,204
-Is it that scary color?
-It's brown.

840
00:35:40,271 --> 00:35:41,706
Can you taste the marinade?

841
00:35:41,772 --> 00:35:44,008
-This? It's too scary.
-Yes.

842
00:35:44,075 --> 00:35:45,643
Just the marinade.

843
00:35:45,710 --> 00:35:48,079
-You have to try it.
-It's this sauce.

844
00:35:48,146 --> 00:35:49,714
Try the marinade.

845
00:35:49,780 --> 00:35:51,149
-Just a little.
-Is it good?

846
00:35:51,215 --> 00:35:53,217
Just a little for now.

847
00:35:53,784 --> 00:35:55,319
HESITANT

848
00:35:55,386 --> 00:35:56,888
It must be spicy.

849
00:35:56,954 --> 00:35:59,891
Is it still spicy,
even though it's not red?

850
00:35:59,957 --> 00:36:02,560
Is it still spicy,
even though it's not red?

851
00:36:04,095 --> 00:36:05,563
Is it not spicy?

852
00:36:06,197 --> 00:36:08,466
-It's good.
-Darn it.

853
00:36:08,533 --> 00:36:11,669
-It's good.
-Darn it. Wait.

854
00:36:12,570 --> 00:36:14,539
Why is it delicious?

855
00:36:14,605 --> 00:36:18,209
-It's good!
-Wait, why is it good?

856
00:36:18,276 --> 00:36:19,744
-It's good.
-Why does it taste good today?

857
00:36:19,810 --> 00:36:23,181
-It's just a bit salty.
-What? Why am I doing this today?

858
00:36:23,247 --> 00:36:25,349
-Pour in some more.
-This is really bad.

859
00:36:25,416 --> 00:36:29,053
This is just good. This was much spicier.

860
00:36:29,120 --> 00:36:30,454
-Cheongyang pepper.
-This is bad.

861
00:36:30,521 --> 00:36:33,791
It tastes spicy later,
but this is still spicier.

862
00:36:33,858 --> 00:36:35,259
Keun-suk, two minutes.

863
00:36:35,326 --> 00:36:37,695
HE ADDS MORE SPICINESS TOO

864
00:36:38,262 --> 00:36:40,698
4. ADD GROUND PEPPER
AND LEMON JUICE TO THE PAELLA

865
00:36:40,765 --> 00:36:42,433
He adds the tangy flavor.

866
00:36:42,500 --> 00:36:44,802
Keun-suk throws in lemon juice.

867
00:36:44,869 --> 00:36:48,005
It's important to end the round first.

868
00:36:48,072 --> 00:36:51,609
Jae-joong may not think
the second dish is as spicy.

869
00:36:51,676 --> 00:36:52,944
You have 1 minute and 15 seconds.

870
00:36:53,010 --> 00:36:54,378
-Damn.
-A minute and 15 seconds.

871
00:36:54,445 --> 00:36:56,314
-Wait.
-He lays out lettuce.

872
00:36:56,380 --> 00:36:59,383
-This is bad.
-Poong keeps saying something is bad.

873
00:36:59,450 --> 00:37:01,752
You have under one minute left.

874
00:37:01,819 --> 00:37:03,154
Keun-suk, you need to finish up too.

875
00:37:03,221 --> 00:37:06,157
-Keun-suk's dish looks great.
-Yes.

876
00:37:06,224 --> 00:37:07,825
He still looks calm.

877
00:37:07,892 --> 00:37:09,160
But Poong is in trouble.

878
00:37:10,061 --> 00:37:11,362
He can't do that one.

879
00:37:11,429 --> 00:37:13,931
But Poong is in trouble.
He looks too busy.

880
00:37:13,998 --> 00:37:15,800
-Thirty seconds.
-You have thirty seconds.

881
00:37:15,866 --> 00:37:18,169
He got the rice.

882
00:37:18,236 --> 00:37:21,239
And he tops it off with powder.

883
00:37:21,305 --> 00:37:23,441
You have 20 seconds now.

884
00:37:23,507 --> 00:37:25,543
Keun-suk, you have 15 seconds.

885
00:37:25,610 --> 00:37:28,546
You have to finish up now.

886
00:37:28,613 --> 00:37:32,416
-Wait, can I pull this off?
-Fifteen seconds. You have to finish up.

887
00:37:32,483 --> 00:37:33,884
Can I make it?

888
00:37:34,719 --> 00:37:36,721
-Can I make it?
-Raw squid?

889
00:37:36,787 --> 00:37:38,990
Ten. Nine. Eight. Seven.

890
00:37:39,056 --> 00:37:40,891
-Six.
-What is that?

891
00:37:40,958 --> 00:37:43,761
Five. Four. Keun-suk finishes first.

892
00:37:43,828 --> 00:37:45,696
Keun-suk finishes first.

893
00:37:45,763 --> 00:37:48,199
-Why did the squid go in here?
-Come on!

894
00:37:48,266 --> 00:37:51,702
Time's up!

895
00:37:51,769 --> 00:37:54,038
-He couldn't ring the bell.
-Why did it end after this went in?

896
00:37:54,105 --> 00:37:55,773
What do you want to do with this?

897
00:37:55,840 --> 00:37:58,109
Hey, wait.

898
00:37:58,175 --> 00:37:59,810
-Why is this in here?
-Why is it in here?

899
00:37:59,877 --> 00:38:02,346
-I see.
-Why is it in here?

900
00:38:02,413 --> 00:38:03,881
-Right.
-Why?

901
00:38:03,948 --> 00:38:05,483
-What?
-Did you have to cut this?

902
00:38:05,549 --> 00:38:06,884
My hand slipped, and it fell in.

903
00:38:06,951 --> 00:38:09,587
-So? Will you pull it out or leave it in?
-No.

904
00:38:09,654 --> 00:38:11,155
-Well, I…
-So?

905
00:38:11,222 --> 00:38:12,657
In or out?

906
00:38:12,723 --> 00:38:15,559
-May I pull it out?
-If you don't need it, do that.

907
00:38:15,626 --> 00:38:18,896
-Should I do that? No way.
-He's buying time to cook it.

908
00:38:18,963 --> 00:38:20,264
-May I pull it out?
-You may.

909
00:38:20,331 --> 00:38:23,267
Then I'll pull it out,
so please do understand.

910
00:38:23,334 --> 00:38:24,902
-It's not a new dish.
-I'm so sorry.

911
00:38:24,969 --> 00:38:28,506
-You can. I'll let you do that.
-I see. Thank you.

912
00:38:28,572 --> 00:38:30,708
Wait, give me that.

913
00:38:31,275 --> 00:38:33,577
THE SQUID WAS COOKED WELL
THANKS TO THAT SKIT

914
00:38:33,644 --> 00:38:36,847
-Ring the bell.
-Okay.

915
00:38:36,914 --> 00:38:39,550
Poong is done too.

916
00:38:39,617 --> 00:38:41,986
What did you do toward the end?

917
00:38:42,053 --> 00:38:45,323
-What about this? The soup.
-I served it. Darn it. Wait.

918
00:38:45,389 --> 00:38:47,291
-He ran out of time.
-He ran out of time.

919
00:38:47,358 --> 00:38:49,627
-I couldn't even taste it.
-He didn't taste it.

920
00:38:49,694 --> 00:38:52,063
He couldn't even taste the soup.

921
00:38:52,129 --> 00:38:53,764
THE KNOCKOFF
VS KNOCKOUT ROUND IS OVER

922
00:38:53,831 --> 00:38:55,800
The opening game
of the Big Asian Competition.

923
00:38:55,866 --> 00:38:59,937
Both dishes were completed for Jae-joong.

924
00:39:00,004 --> 00:39:03,941
Jong-won and Hyun-suk were
surprised to see Keun-suk's skills.

925
00:39:04,008 --> 00:39:06,210
It seemed like he had
lots of experiences in cooking.

926
00:39:06,277 --> 00:39:08,679
I could tell by how he used the knife

927
00:39:08,746 --> 00:39:11,382
and how he didn't pour in
all of the broth at once.

928
00:39:11,449 --> 00:39:14,318
He kept his eyes on the dish
and watched as he poured more in.

929
00:39:14,385 --> 00:39:16,987
Only those who have experience
would know to do that.

930
00:39:17,054 --> 00:39:18,489
I see.

931
00:39:18,556 --> 00:39:22,126
I didn't think he could
make paella with instant rice,

932
00:39:22,193 --> 00:39:26,130
-but it obviously looks like it.
-It's perfect.

933
00:39:26,197 --> 00:39:29,200
Look at Keun-suk,
standing with both hands clasped.

934
00:39:29,266 --> 00:39:31,235
-He looks modest.
-How modest.

935
00:39:31,302 --> 00:39:34,605
-It's great to see him like this.
-Isn't it?

936
00:39:35,940 --> 00:39:39,410
SPICY PAELLA WITH LOTS OF SQUID

937
00:39:40,144 --> 00:39:43,314
MADE BY A COOK
WHO CAN'T FEEL SPICINESS

938
00:39:44,181 --> 00:39:48,252
JANG KEUN-SUK'S SURREALLY SPICY

939
00:39:48,319 --> 00:39:50,588
-It doesn't look too spicy.
-Right?

940
00:39:50,654 --> 00:39:52,923
-Now, it's your turn to try it.
-Okay.

941
00:39:52,990 --> 00:39:54,258
I'm looking forward to this.

942
00:39:55,459 --> 00:39:56,927
First of all, it smells good.

943
00:39:57,495 --> 00:40:01,298
-I want to give him 100 points.
-He gets 100 points for the smell.

944
00:40:01,365 --> 00:40:04,301
-It smells like paella.
-It does?

945
00:40:04,368 --> 00:40:07,872
-This is a wonder.
-He used curry powder and all.

946
00:40:08,973 --> 00:40:10,541
He took a bite.

947
00:40:11,175 --> 00:40:13,177
SMILING

948
00:40:13,244 --> 00:40:15,346
It's called Surreally Spicy.

949
00:40:15,413 --> 00:40:17,548
His expression is confusing.

950
00:40:17,615 --> 00:40:18,616
SAVORING

951
00:40:18,682 --> 00:40:20,251
-I see.
-Mmm.

952
00:40:20,317 --> 00:40:23,754
-You're good.
-I see. He's good?

953
00:40:23,821 --> 00:40:25,623
It's seasoned perfectly.

954
00:40:25,689 --> 00:40:29,693
He probably used spicy sauce
he had never used before,

955
00:40:29,760 --> 00:40:31,629
but still, how did he season it this well?

956
00:40:31,695 --> 00:40:32,897
How spicy is it for you?

957
00:40:32,963 --> 00:40:35,232
It's great. I love it.

958
00:40:35,299 --> 00:40:38,202
-Does it make you just sweat a bit?
-It's probably quite spicy.

959
00:40:38,269 --> 00:40:41,372
The mix of sauce and ingredients

960
00:40:41,439 --> 00:40:45,075
all came together nicely,
and I can taste them all.

961
00:40:45,142 --> 00:40:47,945
He pulls out the Manila clam meat.

962
00:40:48,012 --> 00:40:50,614
He loves squid,

963
00:40:50,681 --> 00:40:53,150
and he's an expert at it.

964
00:40:53,217 --> 00:40:54,885
He tries Manila clam and shrimp.

965
00:40:54,952 --> 00:40:57,955
-He eats so well.
-So? How is it?

966
00:40:58,022 --> 00:41:01,258
This is even better than
what I had in Spain.

967
00:41:01,325 --> 00:41:03,527
It was better than Spanish paella.

968
00:41:03,594 --> 00:41:05,362
HIS SHOWOFF SIDE
GETS SLOWLY RECHARGED

969
00:41:06,330 --> 00:41:08,732
I hope he makes this for me again.

970
00:41:08,799 --> 00:41:11,001
-He wants Keun-suk to make it again.
-I mean it.

971
00:41:11,068 --> 00:41:13,037
-Anytime.
-He's sweating.

972
00:41:13,103 --> 00:41:15,473
-But there's one thing.
-He's sorry for something.

973
00:41:15,539 --> 00:41:16,574
Is it not as spicy?

974
00:41:16,640 --> 00:41:19,944
I think he put the squid in
a little too fast.

975
00:41:20,010 --> 00:41:22,112
-Is it tough?
-It became a bit tough.

976
00:41:22,179 --> 00:41:23,848
The squid turned out too hard.

977
00:41:23,914 --> 00:41:26,484
He checks the texture too.

978
00:41:26,550 --> 00:41:28,052
I'll use fresh squid next time.

979
00:41:28,118 --> 00:41:29,587
He'll use fresh squid next time.

980
00:41:29,653 --> 00:41:32,323
-But still, it just tastes good.
-I see.

981
00:41:32,389 --> 00:41:34,925
-I think I can finish this.
-Really?

982
00:41:34,992 --> 00:41:37,795
-Yes, it's really good.
-It's really good.

983
00:41:37,862 --> 00:41:42,333
Keun-suk, you're more likely
to win the star today.

984
00:41:42,399 --> 00:41:44,635
I think the star is
moving toward Keun-suk.

985
00:41:44,702 --> 00:41:46,837
STAR, YOU'RE JUST LIKE ME…
ARE YOU OVER THERE?

986
00:41:47,404 --> 00:41:51,242
STIR-FRIED SQUID IN WRAPS

987
00:41:52,009 --> 00:41:56,514
SPICY MARINADE
MADE WITH CHEONGYANG PEPPER AND MALA

988
00:41:57,081 --> 00:42:00,918
WEBTOON ARTIST KIM POONG'S
HOTTES-QUID IN ASIA

989
00:42:02,286 --> 00:42:03,687
How is he supposed to eat this?

990
00:42:03,754 --> 00:42:07,358
Turn it into a wrap with rice,
squid, radish, and bean sprouts.

991
00:42:07,424 --> 00:42:09,627
-There's radish in there.
-Yes.

992
00:42:09,693 --> 00:42:11,729
-May I try the soup first?
-Sure.

993
00:42:11,795 --> 00:42:14,198
He didn't even get to taste it.

994
00:42:14,265 --> 00:42:15,633
I think it'll taste good.

995
00:42:16,667 --> 00:42:17,868
How's the soup?

996
00:42:18,836 --> 00:42:20,404
-Gosh.
-Whoa.

997
00:42:21,472 --> 00:42:22,973
It tastes like MSG.

998
00:42:23,874 --> 00:42:26,110
-Exactly.
-It has to be delicious.

999
00:42:26,176 --> 00:42:27,411
It's really good.

1000
00:42:27,478 --> 00:42:29,914
There's a lot, so may I try a bite too?

1001
00:42:29,980 --> 00:42:33,684
I'm right here, so let me
tell the viewers what it's like.

1002
00:42:33,751 --> 00:42:34,785
SLURP

1003
00:42:35,352 --> 00:42:36,954
It's good.

1004
00:42:37,021 --> 00:42:38,522
The soup tastes great.

1005
00:42:38,589 --> 00:42:40,124
Now, the main dish.

1006
00:42:40,190 --> 00:42:42,526
-Let me try it separately once.
-Sure.

1007
00:42:42,593 --> 00:42:44,929
HE TRIES JUST THE SQUID FIRST

1008
00:42:46,263 --> 00:42:48,198
SMILING

1009
00:42:48,933 --> 00:42:51,869
I can't tell what he means by that face.

1010
00:42:51,936 --> 00:42:54,038
-Is it good?
-Is it too spicy?

1011
00:42:54,104 --> 00:42:56,373
-It's not too spicy.
-It's not?

1012
00:42:56,440 --> 00:42:58,509
-It's not spicy?
-He loves squid,

1013
00:42:58,576 --> 00:43:00,311
so the texture must be nice.

1014
00:43:02,046 --> 00:43:04,214
-He tries the soup again.
-Is it spicy?

1015
00:43:04,281 --> 00:43:05,783
-The guests all smile
-Is it too salty?

1016
00:43:05,849 --> 00:43:08,752
-whenever they try Poong's dish.
-Yes.

1017
00:43:08,819 --> 00:43:10,220
IS HE HAPPY?

1018
00:43:10,788 --> 00:43:13,023
-Honestly speaking, it's a bit salty.
-Too salty?

1019
00:43:13,090 --> 00:43:14,091
It's a bit salty.

1020
00:43:14,158 --> 00:43:17,428
I'm sure you gave me the lettuce
to make wraps…

1021
00:43:17,494 --> 00:43:18,996
-That and rice.
-And…

1022
00:43:19,063 --> 00:43:21,398
-It'll be fine as a wrap.
-You should…

1023
00:43:21,465 --> 00:43:22,600
Poong is walking over.

1024
00:43:22,666 --> 00:43:26,303
Also, the squid on the dish was

1025
00:43:26,370 --> 00:43:27,571
for you to eat.

1026
00:43:27,638 --> 00:43:29,173
I see.

1027
00:43:29,239 --> 00:43:31,575
You can try the top part.

1028
00:43:31,642 --> 00:43:36,513
You had a plan all along. It
could be too spicy, so you served that.

1029
00:43:36,580 --> 00:43:39,783
You can put that in
and wrap it all together.

1030
00:43:39,850 --> 00:43:44,121
-That and the bean sprouts. And rice.
-And rice.

1031
00:43:44,188 --> 00:43:45,389
Is this how he should eat it?

1032
00:43:45,456 --> 00:43:46,790
-Yes, that's right.
-Okay.

1033
00:43:47,358 --> 00:43:49,727
HE CAREFULLY TRIES
HIS FIRST WRAP

1034
00:43:49,793 --> 00:43:51,895
Jae-joong is a gourmet.

1035
00:43:51,962 --> 00:43:53,230
CAREFUL

1036
00:43:53,297 --> 00:43:55,099
He begins to nod.

1037
00:43:55,165 --> 00:43:56,500
Is it not as salty?

1038
00:43:56,567 --> 00:43:58,702
Is it okay? Does it go well?

1039
00:43:58,769 --> 00:44:00,771
-The saltiness disappeared.
-It did?

1040
00:44:00,838 --> 00:44:03,140
-That was why he made it into a wrap.
-You're right.

1041
00:44:03,207 --> 00:44:05,943
That was why he served
bean sprouts and the whole squid.

1042
00:44:06,010 --> 00:44:08,646
-I'll try it with perilla leaf.
-The perilla leaf.

1043
00:44:09,813 --> 00:44:11,248
CRUNCHY

1044
00:44:12,282 --> 00:44:13,617
IS HE TROUBLED?

1045
00:44:13,684 --> 00:44:15,486
OR IS IT GOOD?

1046
00:44:15,552 --> 00:44:16,854
What's new? Is it okay?

1047
00:44:18,355 --> 00:44:21,125
-It tastes different.
-It tastes different?

1048
00:44:21,191 --> 00:44:23,927
But is it not as spicy as you like it?

1049
00:44:23,994 --> 00:44:27,264
I was looking forward to eating
something more Korean.

1050
00:44:27,331 --> 00:44:29,566
He mentioned Sokcho-style and all.

1051
00:44:29,633 --> 00:44:31,201
But it doesn't taste Korean.

1052
00:44:31,268 --> 00:44:35,873
I think he brought out
more flavors from Chinese cuisine.

1053
00:44:35,939 --> 00:44:37,174
Did you mean to do this?

1054
00:44:37,241 --> 00:44:38,442
Of course.

1055
00:44:38,509 --> 00:44:40,377
He wanted a new kind of dish.

1056
00:44:40,444 --> 00:44:43,247
It might work with Sung-hoon.

1057
00:44:43,313 --> 00:44:45,349
Yes, Sung-hoon.

1058
00:44:45,416 --> 00:44:48,552
Sung-hoon will try Poong's dish first.

1059
00:44:49,119 --> 00:44:50,120
CONCERNED

1060
00:44:50,487 --> 00:44:52,389
-It's very unique.
-It is?

1061
00:44:53,257 --> 00:44:54,825
Aren't you putting in too much?

1062
00:44:54,892 --> 00:44:56,393
-Give him bean sprouts.
-Yes, bean sprouts.

1063
00:44:56,460 --> 00:44:58,962
-Bean sprouts.
-He adds more bean sprouts.

1064
00:44:59,563 --> 00:45:02,399
-Thanks a lot.
-Sung-hoon tries the wrap too.

1065
00:45:02,466 --> 00:45:06,270
I wonder how Sung-hoon will take
the spicy dish.

1066
00:45:07,104 --> 00:45:11,475
Look how serious he is.

1067
00:45:12,142 --> 00:45:14,478
What if he runs over to Poong?

1068
00:45:15,345 --> 00:45:18,015
-Gosh.
-It must be spicy.

1069
00:45:18,082 --> 00:45:20,050
Is it spicy?

1070
00:45:20,117 --> 00:45:24,354
-It's spicy to me.
-Of course, it is.

1071
00:45:24,421 --> 00:45:26,390
Gosh, man.

1072
00:45:26,457 --> 00:45:27,458
It must be quite spicy.

1073
00:45:28,025 --> 00:45:30,327
SHOULD I TAKE HIM DOWN?

1074
00:45:30,394 --> 00:45:32,796
This is a tough dish
for normal people to swallow.

1075
00:45:33,297 --> 00:45:37,334
-Right?
-His level of spiciness is too high.

1076
00:45:38,235 --> 00:45:39,970
-I can already tell by his face.
-This is…

1077
00:45:41,238 --> 00:45:42,339
GASPING

1078
00:45:42,406 --> 00:45:44,274
He looks mad.

1079
00:45:44,842 --> 00:45:46,477
Don't mess with him right now.

1080
00:45:47,077 --> 00:45:48,312
-I say…
-Yes?

1081
00:45:49,213 --> 00:45:53,050
-This was what he was like in America.
-Is it spicy?

1082
00:45:53,117 --> 00:45:54,451
The spiciness is fine.

1083
00:45:54,518 --> 00:45:58,722
But I'd prefer it if there were
more flavors, like sweetness.

1084
00:45:58,789 --> 00:46:02,826
But it's just spiciness
without any other flavors.

1085
00:46:04,461 --> 00:46:05,562
I want to try it.

1086
00:46:05,629 --> 00:46:08,999
Please try Keun-suk's dish too.

1087
00:46:10,667 --> 00:46:12,336
ABOUT TO ATTACK!

1088
00:46:13,103 --> 00:46:14,772
That's also spicy.

1089
00:46:14,838 --> 00:46:16,507
-This one too?
-Yes.

1090
00:46:16,573 --> 00:46:17,875
Thank you for the food.

1091
00:46:19,209 --> 00:46:20,644
A BITE

1092
00:46:22,212 --> 00:46:23,213
CURIOUS

1093
00:46:23,781 --> 00:46:25,449
-Is it not spicy?
-He'll get mad.

1094
00:46:25,516 --> 00:46:26,517
SNIFFLE

1095
00:46:26,583 --> 00:46:29,119
Is it spicy yet delicious?

1096
00:46:29,186 --> 00:46:30,420
A BIG BITE

1097
00:46:30,487 --> 00:46:31,922
SLURP

1098
00:46:31,989 --> 00:46:33,457
But it must be spicy.

1099
00:46:33,524 --> 00:46:35,659
BRUTAL

1100
00:46:35,726 --> 00:46:37,161
I won't steal it from you.

1101
00:46:37,227 --> 00:46:38,629
He keeps turning redder.

1102
00:46:38,695 --> 00:46:39,797
I won't take it from you.

1103
00:46:39,863 --> 00:46:40,864
THE SHRIMP!

1104
00:46:42,566 --> 00:46:44,134
SEXYYAMA

1105
00:46:44,201 --> 00:46:45,836
It's an eating show of a beast.

1106
00:46:45,903 --> 00:46:48,672
I want to throw in some more lemon.

1107
00:46:49,339 --> 00:46:51,208
POURING

1108
00:46:51,275 --> 00:46:54,444
The lemon got destroyed.

1109
00:46:54,511 --> 00:46:57,214
I've never seen anyone
who juiced lemon like that.

1110
00:46:57,281 --> 00:46:59,750
SAVORING

1111
00:46:59,817 --> 00:47:02,186
-The lemon juice must've worked.
-He liked it.

1112
00:47:02,252 --> 00:47:04,021
It's even better with lemon juice.

1113
00:47:05,889 --> 00:47:08,425
Press one for Jang Keun-suk.

1114
00:47:08,492 --> 00:47:10,961
Press two for Kim Poong.

1115
00:47:11,028 --> 00:47:12,429
I don't know who'll win.

1116
00:47:12,496 --> 00:47:17,034
-There may be a twist.
-Yes, you never know.

1117
00:47:17,100 --> 00:47:18,902
-I pressed it.
-You did?

1118
00:47:18,969 --> 00:47:20,304
Let's find out!

1119
00:47:20,971 --> 00:47:22,906
Asia's spiciest.

1120
00:47:22,973 --> 00:47:26,443
This was the opening game
for the Big Asian Competition.

1121
00:47:26,510 --> 00:47:30,547
Poong and Keun-suk fought to make
Asia's spiciest dish.

1122
00:47:30,614 --> 00:47:33,917
Which one did Jae-joong choose?

1123
00:47:33,984 --> 00:47:36,420
Show us his choice!

1124
00:47:36,486 --> 00:47:38,922
JANG KEUN-SUK WINS

1125
00:47:38,989 --> 00:47:42,459
JANG KEUN-SUK'S
SURREALLY SPICY WINS

1126
00:47:42,526 --> 00:47:46,496
-That was unexpected.
-Keun-suk wins.

1127
00:47:46,563 --> 00:47:48,832
He could probably sell it at a restaurant.

1128
00:47:48,899 --> 00:47:50,167
It was absolutely delicious.

1129
00:47:50,734 --> 00:47:52,035
THANK YOU

1130
00:47:52,102 --> 00:47:54,304
-I'll grow to like the dish too.
-I see.

1131
00:47:55,272 --> 00:47:56,273
I'm off to a great start.

1132
00:47:56,340 --> 00:47:57,574
If you let me have the open spot…

1133
00:47:59,076 --> 00:48:01,812
-I'll be waiting every week.
-Okay.

1134
00:48:01,879 --> 00:48:04,982
Poong is in danger of losing his spot.

1135
00:48:06,116 --> 00:48:07,517
Please put the star on him.

1136
00:48:09,453 --> 00:48:10,754
Man, it's spicy.

1137
00:48:10,821 --> 00:48:13,090
-It's good. It was really good.
-It must be spicy.

1138
00:48:13,156 --> 00:48:14,925
My nose is runny now.

1139
00:48:14,992 --> 00:48:17,661
-Congratulations, Keun-suk!
-I'll make it for you again next time.

1140
00:48:18,462 --> 00:48:20,464
He wins his first star.

1141
00:48:22,132 --> 00:48:24,201
AN APOLOGY
TO THE KNOCKOFF CHEF TOO

1142
00:48:24,268 --> 00:48:27,137
<i>This is the second round</i>
<i>of the big Asian chefs' competition</i>

1143
00:48:27,204 --> 00:48:30,774
<i>by using Jae-joong's ingredients.</i>

1144
00:48:30,841 --> 00:48:34,311
The crazy chef of Singapore,
Chef Han Li Guang is up.

1145
00:48:34,378 --> 00:48:38,749
He's up against Choi Hyun-suk,
the crazy chef of <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>.

1146
00:48:38,815 --> 00:48:42,653
Chef Li Guang singled out
Chef Hyun-suk as his opponent.

1147
00:48:42,719 --> 00:48:44,588
He won't deal with the small fish.

1148
00:48:44,655 --> 00:48:46,490
-He's here to take the big one.
-I want the head.

1149
00:48:46,556 --> 00:48:48,325
He must think
he can easily win against Hyun-suk.

1150
00:48:48,392 --> 00:48:49,960
Isn't that so?

1151
00:48:50,027 --> 00:48:53,130
I think Chef Hyun-suk is
a legend on the show.

1152
00:48:53,196 --> 00:48:55,766
So actually, I think
he's one of the hardest to beat.

1153
00:48:55,832 --> 00:49:00,137
But I wanted to challenge myself
and battle against the legend.

1154
00:49:00,203 --> 00:49:02,639
-Legendary. That's cool.
-He's a legend.

1155
00:49:02,706 --> 00:49:05,208
Did you begin to think, "What if I lose?"

1156
00:49:05,275 --> 00:49:06,276
I mean, I'm nervous,

1157
00:49:06,343 --> 00:49:08,278
but there's no pressure
against Chef Hyun-suk.

1158
00:49:08,345 --> 00:49:10,447
-Because he'll obviously win.
-Right.

1159
00:49:10,514 --> 00:49:13,216
He wouldn't need to feel anxious.

1160
00:49:13,283 --> 00:49:16,019
-I think he agrees.
-I knew it.

1161
00:49:16,086 --> 00:49:17,888
He says you're right.

1162
00:49:17,955 --> 00:49:20,390
He'll win anyway,
so he doesn't need to get nervous.

1163
00:49:20,457 --> 00:49:22,359
He looks really kind,

1164
00:49:22,426 --> 00:49:24,361
but he must be competitive on the inside.

1165
00:49:24,428 --> 00:49:26,196
I'm sorry, but one second.

1166
00:49:26,263 --> 00:49:28,565
May I borrow your knife, Poong?

1167
00:49:28,632 --> 00:49:30,701
Can you say, "Please allow me to
use it, Mr. Poong, sir."

1168
00:49:31,868 --> 00:49:33,070
Otherwise, no.

1169
00:49:33,136 --> 00:49:36,840
What is this?
Why did you forget to bring your knife?

1170
00:49:36,907 --> 00:49:39,176
I'll let you use it if you ask politely.

1171
00:49:39,242 --> 00:49:40,410
I might need a Chinese kitchen knife,

1172
00:49:40,477 --> 00:49:43,113
but I'll use my hand if he does that.

1173
00:49:44,815 --> 00:49:45,983
You should cooperate.

1174
00:49:46,049 --> 00:49:48,118
Fine. Gosh.

1175
00:49:48,185 --> 00:49:50,120
We have to win against them.

1176
00:49:50,187 --> 00:49:55,292
Chef Li Guang, you also get a perk
as it's your first time on the show.

1177
00:49:55,359 --> 00:49:58,562
Would you like to use the perk?

1178
00:49:58,628 --> 00:49:59,896
Of course, I'll use it.

1179
00:50:01,231 --> 00:50:03,767
GOOD CHOICE, LI GUANG

1180
00:50:03,834 --> 00:50:06,570
-No shame.
-Of course.

1181
00:50:06,636 --> 00:50:09,873
Which one of the three
would you like to use?

1182
00:50:09,940 --> 00:50:11,842
The one-minute stop.

1183
00:50:14,177 --> 00:50:16,980
Gosh, yes. He can't help it.

1184
00:50:17,047 --> 00:50:20,751
He already saw how it worked. Exactly.

1185
00:50:20,817 --> 00:50:23,954
If you think about it,
Chef Li Guang started a bit after me.

1186
00:50:24,021 --> 00:50:26,957
The discipline in the culinary arts
is globally on the demise.

1187
00:50:27,924 --> 00:50:28,925
Right?

1188
00:50:29,693 --> 00:50:31,928
CHEF LI GUANG'S INGREDIENTS: PEAR, CHIVE,
LIQUID SEASONING, PICKLED PERILLA LEAF

1189
00:50:31,995 --> 00:50:34,197
BLUE CRABS, SSAMJANG, BULDAK SAUCE,
SOJU, KIMCHI, KETCHUP, MAKGEOLLI, AND MORE

1190
00:50:34,264 --> 00:50:36,900
Chef Li Guang, what are you making?

1191
00:50:36,967 --> 00:50:41,204
My dish is called
Makgeolli Guang, my name.

1192
00:50:41,271 --> 00:50:45,208
-Han Li Guang, Makgeolli Guang.
-I see.

1193
00:50:45,275 --> 00:50:47,744
I'm a Singaporean, representing Singapore.

1194
00:50:47,811 --> 00:50:50,547
I want to create
Singapore's national dish, chili crab.

1195
00:50:50,614 --> 00:50:52,249
But with a Korean twist,

1196
00:50:52,315 --> 00:50:54,951
to make a dish
Jae-joong will like as well.

1197
00:50:55,018 --> 00:50:56,686
So I'll put squid inside,

1198
00:50:56,753 --> 00:50:59,256
use <i>ssamjang </i>instead,
and I'll use perilla leaves too.

1199
00:50:59,322 --> 00:51:01,925
