the sauce. He needs to.

1432
01:01:06,329 --> 01:01:07,363
Yes, that's right.

1433
01:01:07,430 --> 01:01:10,299
-Chili crab sauce is thick.
-Buldak sauce.

1434
01:01:11,300 --> 01:01:12,902
He put in pickled perilla leaves.

1435
01:01:12,969 --> 01:01:15,071
Five minutes. Jung-hwan!

1436
01:01:15,138 --> 01:01:17,540
-Five minutes.
-Five minutes.

1437
01:01:17,607 --> 01:01:18,708
It's so intriguing.

1438
01:01:18,775 --> 01:01:20,710
I came nearby,

1439
01:01:20,777 --> 01:01:24,147
-and it smells like <i>makgeolli</i>.
-Yes, <i>makgeolli</i>!

1440
01:01:24,213 --> 01:01:26,549
This must be the crab sauce.

1441
01:01:26,616 --> 01:01:28,985
Why don't you try the sauce?

1442
01:01:29,052 --> 01:01:31,354
It'll taste good with the seafood.

1443
01:01:31,421 --> 01:01:33,523
Try it quickly before he puts anything in.

1444
01:01:33,589 --> 01:01:35,725
-Chef Li Guang is…
-What's he doing?

1445
01:01:35,792 --> 01:01:36,926
What's that? A ritual?

1446
01:01:36,993 --> 01:01:39,162
What is that? What's he doing?

1447
01:01:39,228 --> 01:01:40,697
-What's he doing?
-The smell?

1448
01:01:40,763 --> 01:01:42,331
-Does he just need the smell?
-Can I try this?

1449
01:01:42,398 --> 01:01:44,667
It was like some ritual.

1450
01:01:44,734 --> 01:01:47,036
-Can I try this? Tasting.
-Yes.

1451
01:01:47,103 --> 01:01:49,172
It's thick. The thickness is just right.

1452
01:01:49,238 --> 01:01:51,908
Does it taste like
the chili crab sauce we know?

1453
01:01:51,974 --> 01:01:54,644
Does it taste like
the chili crab sauce we know?

1454
01:01:54,711 --> 01:01:56,012
DOES IT TASTE LIKE CHILI CRAB?

1455
01:01:56,079 --> 01:01:57,346
What's it like?

1456
01:01:58,681 --> 01:01:59,682
What's it like?

1457
01:01:59,749 --> 01:02:00,950
We're in Singapore!

1458
01:02:03,619 --> 01:02:04,620
It tastes like it.

1459
01:02:04,687 --> 01:02:06,255
We're in Singapore!

1460
01:02:06,322 --> 01:02:08,558
WE'VE ARRIVED AT THE RIGHT PLACE

1461
01:02:08,624 --> 01:02:10,126
It tastes like it.

1462
01:02:10,193 --> 01:02:11,728
Really? He did that with <i>ssamjang</i>?

1463
01:02:11,794 --> 01:02:16,232
There's a twist of Korean, though.
It's a bit spicier.

1464
01:02:16,299 --> 01:02:18,968
He used Korean ingredients
to recreate the Singaporean taste?

1465
01:02:19,602 --> 01:02:22,105
GETTING ANXIOUS AFTER HEARING
ABOUT ARRIVING IN SINGAPORE

1466
01:02:22,672 --> 01:02:24,807
OPENING THE COOKED SUNDAE

1467
01:02:24,874 --> 01:02:27,477
It's cooked. Wait, maybe not the inside.

1468
01:02:27,543 --> 01:02:28,978
The <i>sundae </i>is out.

1469
01:02:29,045 --> 01:02:30,079
Isn't it undercooked?

1470
01:02:30,146 --> 01:02:32,715
He'll coat it with starch.

1471
01:02:32,782 --> 01:02:35,384
-Will he fry it?
-He'll deep-fry it again.

1472
01:02:35,451 --> 01:02:37,720
I knew it, Chef Hyun-suk.

1473
01:02:37,787 --> 01:02:39,922
He's coating it with egg whites too.

1474
01:02:39,989 --> 01:02:42,225
-Jung-hwan.
-Wait, this is…

1475
01:02:42,291 --> 01:02:44,794
-It looks like a worm.
-Wait, it's…

1476
01:02:44,861 --> 01:02:48,030
What is this? Is he copying me?

1477
01:02:48,898 --> 01:02:51,567
They look like worms climbing up the tree!

1478
01:02:51,634 --> 01:02:53,369
Gosh, come on!

1479
01:02:53,870 --> 01:02:55,438
It looks like a worm.

1480
01:02:55,505 --> 01:02:58,541
I think he's copying my worm.

1481
01:02:58,608 --> 01:03:00,543
Isn't that my thing?

1482
01:03:00,610 --> 01:03:02,111
It's going in.

1483
01:03:03,446 --> 01:03:05,882
Chef Li Guang is using eggs too.

1484
01:03:05,948 --> 01:03:07,850
He has kimchi, but he hasn't used it yet.

1485
01:03:07,917 --> 01:03:09,018
Sorry.

1486
01:03:09,085 --> 01:03:10,419
He's putting in eggs.

1487
01:03:11,554 --> 01:03:13,589
-Eggs.
-Yes, I know. This is it.

1488
01:03:13,656 --> 01:03:16,392
He's making it like the chili crab sauce.

1489
01:03:16,459 --> 01:03:17,560
They have three minutes.

1490
01:03:17,627 --> 01:03:19,328
Three minutes left.

1491
01:03:19,896 --> 01:03:22,365
HYUN-SUK ALSO USES STARCH
TO THICKEN THE SAUCE

1492
01:03:22,431 --> 01:03:25,268
-Jung-hwan, try the sauce!
-What?

1493
01:03:25,334 --> 01:03:27,270
Chef Hyun-suk won't give me the way.

1494
01:03:27,336 --> 01:03:28,471
It's in his hand.

1495
01:03:28,538 --> 01:03:31,073
-Yes, I wanted to try it.
-Why are you stopping him?

1496
01:03:31,140 --> 01:03:32,475
I wonder.

1497
01:03:32,542 --> 01:03:34,911
-Chef Hyun-suk runs away.
-Hey!

1498
01:03:34,977 --> 01:03:36,412
I wonder.

1499
01:03:36,479 --> 01:03:38,681
-Chef Hyun-suk runs away.
-Excuse me.

1500
01:03:38,748 --> 01:03:40,783
WHAT'S WITH HIM?

1501
01:03:40,850 --> 01:03:42,852
I feel like a striker against a defender.

1502
01:03:42,919 --> 01:03:45,288
He's screening me out, but why?

1503
01:03:45,354 --> 01:03:47,857
I guess he had to strain that.

1504
01:03:47,924 --> 01:03:48,925
He wants to make it smooth.

1505
01:03:48,991 --> 01:03:51,227
I'll try it after he's done.

1506
01:03:51,994 --> 01:03:53,863
Li Guang is already serving his dish.

1507
01:03:53,930 --> 01:03:57,733
Gosh, this looks good. It looks so good.

1508
01:03:57,800 --> 01:04:00,903
There's the sauce. The sauce!

1509
01:04:00,970 --> 01:04:02,905
-Whoa.
-It looks really nice.

1510
01:04:02,972 --> 01:04:07,043
He put in both squids and crabs.

1511
01:04:07,109 --> 01:04:09,645
-The <i>makgeolli </i>rice cake.
-The toasted <i>makgeolli </i>rice cake.

1512
01:04:09,712 --> 01:04:11,180
-Two minutes.
-Last two minutes!

1513
01:04:11,247 --> 01:04:13,049
-You have two minutes.
-Two minutes.

1514
01:04:13,115 --> 01:04:14,383
The rice cake pieces…

1515
01:04:15,351 --> 01:04:16,552
He decorates with rice cake pieces.

1516
01:04:16,619 --> 01:04:18,554
HIS TREMOR IS BACK

1517
01:04:18,621 --> 01:04:20,723
Okay. Shaking.

1518
01:04:20,790 --> 01:04:21,691
Shaking very much.

1519
01:04:21,757 --> 01:04:23,459
-Li Guang.
-He's that nervous?

1520
01:04:23,526 --> 01:04:26,329
Why are you so nervous?

1521
01:04:26,395 --> 01:04:27,697
He's shaking too much.

1522
01:04:27,763 --> 01:04:30,800
-Li Guang.
-It's okay.

1523
01:04:30,867 --> 01:04:32,768
Li Guang, it's okay.

1524
01:04:32,835 --> 01:04:34,170
You got it.

1525
01:04:34,237 --> 01:04:35,972
-Okay.
-Almost.

1526
01:04:36,038 --> 01:04:39,609
HE STRAINS THE SAUCE

1527
01:04:39,675 --> 01:04:41,844
AND BEGINS TO SERVE THE DISH

1528
01:04:42,411 --> 01:04:44,046
CARROT LEAF

1529
01:04:44,113 --> 01:04:47,550
HE GETS THE LEAF
READY TO DECORATE

1530
01:04:47,617 --> 01:04:49,418
-The sauce.
-A minute and 30 seconds.

1531
01:04:49,485 --> 01:04:52,088
He says I can taste the sauce now.

1532
01:04:52,922 --> 01:04:55,791
Chef Li Guang pulls out the kimchi.

1533
01:04:55,858 --> 01:04:58,127
-Chef Li Guang uses kimchi.
-Kimchi.

1534
01:04:58,194 --> 01:05:00,730
He's rolling it up.

1535
01:05:00,796 --> 01:05:03,900
He put the pear inside and rolled it up.

1536
01:05:03,966 --> 01:05:05,801
And what's that?

1537
01:05:05,868 --> 01:05:08,404
-It's the chive.
-The fluttering chive.

1538
01:05:09,872 --> 01:05:12,275
-That's why he warmed it up?
-Yes.

1539
01:05:12,341 --> 01:05:14,443
EVERYONE'S ATTENTION IS
ON LI GUANG

1540
01:05:14,510 --> 01:05:18,314
He warmed up the chive briefly,
and he's using it to tie that up.

1541
01:05:18,381 --> 01:05:20,283
-He needs you to try it.
-Okay.

1542
01:05:20,349 --> 01:05:21,550
I'll try this.

1543
01:05:21,617 --> 01:05:23,786
Okay, Chef Hyun-suk's sauce.

1544
01:05:23,853 --> 01:05:26,188
-This sauce looks important.
-It must be.

1545
01:05:26,255 --> 01:05:27,790
It smells spicy already.

1546
01:05:27,857 --> 01:05:29,425
You have about a minute left.

1547
01:05:29,492 --> 01:05:33,095
How's the sauce?

1548
01:05:33,162 --> 01:05:34,530
Man, this is…

1549
01:05:35,731 --> 01:05:36,832
What's wrong?

1550
01:05:37,767 --> 01:05:40,036
-Why? Is it bad?
-What's wrong?

1551
01:05:40,102 --> 01:05:41,370
Why? What?

1552
01:05:42,438 --> 01:05:43,673
Did you put a banana in it?

1553
01:05:43,739 --> 01:05:44,740
-Banana milk.
-Right!

1554
01:05:44,807 --> 01:05:48,110
That's why it has soft texture
and a hint of banana.

1555
01:05:48,177 --> 01:05:49,312
It tastes familiar.

1556
01:05:49,378 --> 01:05:51,147
It's good. And spicy.

1557
01:05:51,213 --> 01:05:53,516
You have 40 seconds left.

1558
01:05:53,582 --> 01:05:56,585
HE RELAXES AND BEGINS
TO CUT HIS FOOD

1559
01:05:56,652 --> 01:05:58,721
This one kind of hits you hard,

1560
01:05:58,788 --> 01:06:03,426
but this one tastes mild
after that initial spiciness.

1561
01:06:03,492 --> 01:06:07,396
-It looks pretty.
-He's starting to serve the food.

1562
01:06:07,463 --> 01:06:09,498
-Fifteen seconds.
-Fifteen seconds.

1563
01:06:09,565 --> 01:06:11,367
15 SECONDS?

1564
01:06:11,434 --> 01:06:13,869
-You have 15 seconds.
-Yes.

1565
01:06:15,438 --> 01:06:17,106
-Ten seconds!
-Ten seconds left.

1566
01:06:17,173 --> 01:06:19,375
-Ten seconds. Finish up.
-Nine. Eight.

1567
01:06:19,942 --> 01:06:24,213
HYUN-SUK FINISHES
HIS DECORATION TOO

1568
01:06:24,280 --> 01:06:25,781
-Pull it out.
-Ring the bell.

1569
01:06:25,848 --> 01:06:27,717
-Ring it.
-Five. Four.

1570
01:06:27,783 --> 01:06:30,586
-Chef Li Guang finishes first.
-Okay!

1571
01:06:30,653 --> 01:06:35,024
IT WAS AN INTENSE FIGHT

1572
01:06:35,091 --> 01:06:38,160
-That was amazing.
-Chef Li Guang is covered in sweat.

1573
01:06:38,227 --> 01:06:40,596
AMAZED

1574
01:06:40,663 --> 01:06:43,299
-Sorry for the minute.
-It's okay.

1575
01:06:43,366 --> 01:06:44,433
Never mind it.

1576
01:06:44,500 --> 01:06:47,003
Gosh, he timed it perfectly.

1577
01:06:47,069 --> 01:06:51,574
Both dishes were completed for Jae-joong.

1578
01:06:51,640 --> 01:06:56,645
I didn't want to miss anything they did
while they were cooking.

1579
01:06:56,712 --> 01:06:58,647
It was very thrilling and fun.

1580
01:06:59,548 --> 01:07:03,619
CHILI CRAB MADE
WITH KOREAN INGREDIENTS

1581
01:07:04,687 --> 01:07:08,357
RICE CAKE COVERED WITH MAKGEOLLI
AND PEAR WRAPPED WITH KIMCHI

1582
01:07:09,058 --> 01:07:12,428
CHEF HAN LI GUANG'S
MAKGEOLLI GUANG

1583
01:07:12,495 --> 01:07:15,598
The order was called,
"Do You Know Makgeolli?"

1584
01:07:15,664 --> 01:07:18,634
-It needs to go well with <i>makgeolli</i>.
-It smells so good.

1585
01:07:19,502 --> 01:07:21,570
Let's pair the dish with <i>makgeolli</i>.

1586
01:07:21,637 --> 01:07:24,740
How did he use the boiled <i>makgeolli</i>?

1587
01:07:24,807 --> 01:07:27,476
-The rice cake.
-He dunked them inside.

1588
01:07:27,543 --> 01:07:31,447
<i>He put the rice cake into makgeolli</i>
<i>and had them boiled.</i>

1589
01:07:31,514 --> 01:07:35,117
I've never seen a recipe like this before.

1590
01:07:35,184 --> 01:07:37,720
-I'm so curious.
-Right? I wonder…

1591
01:07:37,787 --> 01:07:40,156
It's coated with <i>makgeolli</i>.

1592
01:07:40,222 --> 01:07:41,690
He put in lots of work.

1593
01:07:42,425 --> 01:07:46,629
It smells like the rice cake was
caramelized by using <i>makgeolli</i>.

1594
01:07:46,695 --> 01:07:48,864
It smells really strong.

1595
01:07:48,931 --> 01:07:51,367
-Really?
-So it must smell strong.

1596
01:07:51,434 --> 01:07:53,135
HE TRIES JUST
THE RICE CAKE FIRST

1597
01:07:53,803 --> 01:07:56,972
CURIOUS

1598
01:07:57,039 --> 01:07:59,275
-Try it with the sauce.
-He reaches for it.

1599
01:07:59,341 --> 01:08:03,546
-The sauce.
-Yes, it may be a bit stiff.

1600
01:08:03,612 --> 01:08:04,613
It's thick.

1601
01:08:04,680 --> 01:08:05,848
He tries it with the sauce.

1602
01:08:08,951 --> 01:08:10,319
Wait, this makes sense.

1603
01:08:11,887 --> 01:08:14,824
-It does? How so?
-My mouth began to water.

1604
01:08:14,890 --> 01:08:16,992
I couldn't imagine something like this.

1605
01:08:17,059 --> 01:08:19,195
-It's a fusion dish.
-It is?

1606
01:08:19,261 --> 01:08:22,865
You eat chili crab with carbs
like fried flower buns,

1607
01:08:22,932 --> 01:08:24,700
so I think he made
something similar to that.

1608
01:08:24,767 --> 01:08:26,402
<i>Yes, it's served with flower buns.</i>

1609
01:08:26,469 --> 01:08:29,171
I think he'll finish the rice cakes.

1610
01:08:29,772 --> 01:08:31,941
-Just smell it.
-"Just smell it"?

1611
01:08:32,007 --> 01:08:34,009
-Just smell it.
-"Just smell it"?

1612
01:08:34,076 --> 01:08:37,746
-So he can't try it?
-He can't.

1613
01:08:37,813 --> 01:08:40,449
I went out to try it,
but he told me to just smell it.

1614
01:08:40,516 --> 01:08:42,351
Just smelling, no eating.

1615
01:08:42,418 --> 01:08:44,920
Just smell it.

1616
01:08:44,987 --> 01:08:48,557
The 25th only smelled
the dish made by 37th place.

1617
01:08:48,624 --> 01:08:49,959
And please dig in.

1618
01:08:50,025 --> 01:08:52,261
HE TRIES THE SQUID FIRST

1619
01:08:52,328 --> 01:08:54,296
I thought he'd try the squid first.

1620
01:08:55,297 --> 01:08:56,465
ANXIOUS

1621
01:08:56,532 --> 01:08:59,235
-It's the flavor of <i>ssamjang</i>.
-Can you taste it?

1622
01:08:59,301 --> 01:09:01,437
-I can feel it.
-I see.

1623
01:09:01,504 --> 01:09:06,175
The mix of <i>ssamjang </i>and chili sauce
works really nicely.

1624
01:09:06,242 --> 01:09:07,810
RELIEVED

1625
01:09:07,877 --> 01:09:10,045
He needs to crave <i>makgeolli</i>.

1626
01:09:11,814 --> 01:09:13,649
-What are you looking for?
-It's…

1627
01:09:13,716 --> 01:09:15,718
I wanted to find the firm part.

1628
01:09:15,784 --> 01:09:17,453
The part between the tentacles
and the trunk?

1629
01:09:17,520 --> 01:09:20,523
-I found it. Right here.
-There it is.

1630
01:09:20,589 --> 01:09:23,259
-He found it.
-The sauce was a bit spicy,

1631
01:09:23,325 --> 01:09:25,127
but he enjoys it so much.

1632
01:09:26,162 --> 01:09:29,165
He especially loves
the texture of that part.

1633
01:09:29,231 --> 01:09:30,699
MOVING

1634
01:09:31,267 --> 01:09:32,735
I suddenly craved the rice cake.

1635
01:09:32,801 --> 01:09:34,837
-Was it automatic?
-Yes.

1636
01:09:34,904 --> 01:09:37,406
But you aren't craving <i>makgeolli</i>.

1637
01:09:37,473 --> 01:09:39,775
Right! He should be craving makgeolli.

1638
01:09:39,842 --> 01:09:41,310
That was a sharp observation.

1639
01:09:41,377 --> 01:09:42,678
LI GUANG GETS FLUSTERED

1640
01:09:42,745 --> 01:09:45,814
-He finally takes a sip.
-He's drinking it.

1641
01:09:45,881 --> 01:09:47,149
He's drinking it.

1642
01:09:47,216 --> 01:09:50,486
-He's drinking.
-It needs to go well with <i>makgeolli</i>.

1643
01:09:52,521 --> 01:09:56,025
-And another bite.
-He needs it as a bar snack.

1644
01:09:56,091 --> 01:09:57,826
A bite of the squid.

1645
01:09:57,893 --> 01:10:01,030
-It looks good. My mouth is watering.
-It does.

1646
01:10:01,096 --> 01:10:02,331
Do they go well?

1647
01:10:02,398 --> 01:10:04,934
The sourness of chili

1648
01:10:05,000 --> 01:10:08,037
and the sweetness of <i>makgeolli</i>

1649
01:10:08,103 --> 01:10:10,806
-go well together.
-They do?

1650
01:10:10,873 --> 01:10:12,341
I was so curious about this.

1651
01:10:12,408 --> 01:10:15,177
He had been saving it.

1652
01:10:15,244 --> 01:10:18,314
-Kimchi, right?
-Kimchi and pear.

1653
01:10:18,380 --> 01:10:20,583
-I wonder what it's like.
-Will he like it?

1654
01:10:21,584 --> 01:10:23,319
CRUNCHY

1655
01:10:23,385 --> 01:10:25,888
Chili sauce and kimchi.

1656
01:10:25,955 --> 01:10:27,990
-Sweet and sour.
-Right?

1657
01:10:28,057 --> 01:10:29,925
-This is so weird.
-Do they go well?

1658
01:10:29,992 --> 01:10:31,994
Why does this all work so well?

1659
01:10:32,061 --> 01:10:34,029
Why does it all work so well?

1660
01:10:34,096 --> 01:10:36,065
I thought it'd taste quite odd,

1661
01:10:36,131 --> 01:10:37,800
but it goes so well,

1662
01:10:37,866 --> 01:10:40,069
it's almost uncanny.

1663
01:10:40,135 --> 01:10:42,838
-Good one, Li Guang.
-This is so oddly good.

1664
01:10:42,905 --> 01:10:46,041
The 37th place. Li Guang.

1665
01:10:46,108 --> 01:10:47,810
-That's why he made it.
-One of the top fifty.

1666
01:10:47,876 --> 01:10:49,011
I wonder what it's like.

1667
01:10:49,078 --> 01:10:52,147
-He tries the perilla leaf.
-I wanted to try that.

1668
01:10:52,214 --> 01:10:56,518
-After eating this, I…
-He craves the rice cake again.

1669
01:10:56,585 --> 01:10:59,355
-He must be craving carbs like rice.
-I guess so.

1670
01:10:59,421 --> 01:11:02,157
-And after rice cake…
-Is it automatic?

1671
01:11:02,224 --> 01:11:04,827
